1
00:00:10,011 --> 00:00:21,011
The Sound of Music - 1965
【音乐之声】

2
00:02:43,930 --> 00:02:46,763
The hills are alive
群山因为音乐…

3
00:02:46,933 --> 00:02:51,358
With the sound of music
充满生气

4
00:02:51,604 --> 00:02:54,095
With songs they have sung
唱了…

5
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:59,198
For a thousand years
千年的歌

6
00:02:59,445 --> 00:03:02,608
The hills fill my heart
群山让我的心中…

7
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:07,411
With the sound of music
充满了音乐

8
00:03:07,654 --> 00:03:14,844
My heart wants to sing Every song it hears
要唱出每支歌

9
00:03:15,361 --> 00:03:20,151
My heart wants to beat like the wings Of the birds that rise
我心震荡像鸟儿翅膀

10
00:03:20,433 --> 00:03:23,493
From the lake to the trees
由湖边飞上树

11
00:03:23,770 --> 00:03:28,059
My heart wants to sigh Like a chime that flies
我心叹息

12
00:03:28,308 --> 00:03:32,267
From a church on a breeze
像钟声飘扬

13
00:03:32,512 --> 00:03:36,004
To laugh like a brook When it trips and falls
笑声像小溪流过石头

14
00:03:36,282 --> 00:03:39,774
Over stones on its way
跌荡抑扬

15
00:03:40,019 --> 00:03:43,910
To sing through the night
夜晚歌唱

16
00:03:44,157 --> 00:03:47,945
Like a lark who is learning to pray
像云雀祈祷

17
00:03:48,294 --> 00:03:53,891
I go to the hills
当我奔向山里

18
00:03:54,133 --> 00:04:00,299
When my heart is lonely
心情落寞

19
00:04:00,540 --> 00:04:03,703
I know I will hear
我听到…

20
00:04:03,876 --> 00:04:09,187
What I've heard before
昔日歌声

21
00:04:09,415 --> 00:04:14,148
My heart will be blessed
我心就会歌唱

22
00:04:14,354 --> 00:04:22,181
With the sound of music
因为音乐的响起

23
00:04:23,196 --> 00:04:28,327
And I'll sing...
我要再度…

24
00:04:28,568 --> 00:04:37,533
...once more
歌唱

25
00:05:13,513 --> 00:05:18,303
《音乐之声》

26
00:07:27,146 --> 00:07:32,641
（萨尔斯堡，奥地利 30年代黄金时期）

27
00:09:19,592 --> 00:09:24,552
Hallelujah, hallelujah
哈利路亚，哈利路亚

28
00:09:24,797 --> 00:09:29,427
Hallelujah, hallelujah
哈利路亚，哈利路亚

29
00:09:31,804 --> 00:09:33,795
- Reverend Mother. - Sister Bernice.
-院长 -柏尼丝修女

30
00:09:34,073 --> 00:09:36,633
- I simply cannot find her. - Maria?
-我找不到她 -犸莉亚？

31
00:09:37,777 --> 00:09:39,074
She's missing again.
她又不见了

32
00:09:39,946 --> 00:09:42,335
We should've put a cowbell around her neck.
也许我们该在她脖子上 挂个牛铃

33
00:09:42,615 --> 00:09:45,641
Have you tried the barn? You know how much she adores the animals.
你找过仓了吗？ 她很喜欢动物

34
00:09:45,918 --> 00:09:48,648
I have looked everywhere. In all of the usual places.
我到处都找过了

35
00:09:48,854 --> 00:09:51,118
Sister, considering it's Maria...
修女，你要知道她是莉亚…

36
00:09:51,357 --> 00:09:53,985
...I suggest you look in someplace unusual.
我建议你找不寻常的地方

37
00:09:59,298 --> 00:10:00,629
Well, Reverend Mother...
院长…

38
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,496
...I hope this new infraction ends whatever doubts...
我希望这次违规 会结束

39
00:10:03,669 --> 00:10:06,934
...you may still have about Maria's future here.
你对她在这里 会有未来的疑虑

40
00:10:07,139 --> 00:10:11,166
I always try to keep faith in my doubts, Sister Berthe.
我对疑虑仍常保持信心

41
00:10:11,444 --> 00:10:14,299
After all, the wool of a black sheep is just as warm.
毕竟黑羊的毛也是会温暖

42
00:10:14,547 --> 00:10:18,836
We are not talking about sheep, black or white, Sister Margaretta.
我们不是争论绵羊颜色

43
00:10:19,118 --> 00:10:22,508
Of all the candidates for the novitiate, Maria is the least...
所有修女的候选人中她最糟

44
00:10:22,788 --> 00:10:25,313
Children, children.
各位…

45
00:10:25,791 --> 00:10:29,750
We were speculating about the qualifications of our postulants.
我们想了解在修道院的各人 表现如何

46
00:10:30,363 --> 00:10:33,355
The Mistress of Novices and the Mistress of Postulants...
见习修女和修道院修女的主管

47
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:38,889
...were trying to help me by expressing opposite points of view.
表达了不同的意见来协助我

48
00:10:39,171 --> 00:10:42,197
Tell me, Sister Catherine, what do you think of Maria?
凯萨琳修女，告诉我 你认为犸莉亚如何？

49
00:10:42,408 --> 00:10:44,672
She's a wonderful girl, some of the time.
她有时候是个好女孩

50
00:10:46,746 --> 00:10:49,544
- Sister Agatha? - It's very easy to like Maria...
-雅嘉佛修女？ -犸莉亚讨人喜欢

51
00:10:49,815 --> 00:10:52,340
...except when it's difficult.
但有时候却不易相处

52
00:10:52,585 --> 00:10:56,180
- And you, Sister Sophia? - Oh, I love her very dearly.
-苏菲亚修女，你呢？ -我喜欢她

53
00:10:56,389 --> 00:10:59,313
But she always seems to be in trouble, doesn't she?
但她爱惹麻烦

54
00:10:59,558 --> 00:11:01,321
Exactly what I say.
这就是我要说的

55
00:11:01,661 --> 00:11:04,084
She climbs a tree and scrapes her knee
她会爬树伤了膝盖

56
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:06,025
Her dress has got a tear
衣服裂开

57
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:10,830
She waltzes on her way to Mass And whistles on the stair
在往弥撒的路上跳华尔兹 在阶梯上吹口哨

58
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:15,929
And underneath her wimple She has curlers in her hair
帽巾下，头发会卷着发卷

59
00:11:16,242 --> 00:11:20,872
I've even heard her singing In the abbey
她会在修道院内唱歌

60
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:23,071
She's always late for chapel
她上教堂总是迟到

61
00:11:23,315 --> 00:11:25,579
But her penitence is real
可是悔却出自真心

62
00:11:25,885 --> 00:11:28,217
She's always late for everything
她做什么都迟到

63
00:11:28,421 --> 00:11:30,446
Except for every meal
但每餐饭从不迟到

64
00:11:30,856 --> 00:11:35,555
I hate to have to say it But I very firmly feel
我不愿说，但我深深觉得

65
00:11:35,761 --> 00:11:40,221
Maria's not an asset to the abbey
犸莉亚不适合修道院

66
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:43,225
I'd like to say a word in her behalf
我愿为她说句好话

67
00:11:43,469 --> 00:11:44,834
Say it, Sister Margaretta.
请说，犸格丽特修女

68
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:49,630
Maria makes me laugh
犸莉亚令我发笑

69
00:11:52,578 --> 00:11:56,435
How do you solve a problem like Maria?
你要如何处理 像犸莉亚这样的问题人物？

70
00:11:56,716 --> 00:12:00,538
How do you catch a cloud And pin it down?
你要如何摘下浮云 然后钉牢？

71
00:12:00,786 --> 00:12:04,142
How do you find a word That means Maria?
你要如何用言语形容她？

72
00:12:04,657 --> 00:12:05,783
A flibbertigibbet
捣蛋鬼！

73
00:12:05,991 --> 00:12:07,390
- A will-o'-the-wisp - A clown
-鬼灵精 -小丑

74
00:12:08,994 --> 00:12:12,760
Many a thing you know You'd like to tell her
许多事你们想告诉她

75
00:12:12,998 --> 00:12:16,422
Many a thing she ought to understand
许多事她该明t

76
00:12:16,902 --> 00:12:20,599
But how do you make her stay And listen to all you say?
但如何使她停下听你说完？

77
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:24,632
How do you keep a wave upon the sand?
如何使海浪停留在沙滩上？

78
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:28,937
How do you solve a problem like Maria?
你要如何处理 像犸莉亚这样的问题人物？

79
00:12:29,482 --> 00:12:35,011
How do you hold a moonbeam...
如何使月光在…

80
00:12:35,254 --> 00:12:40,681
...in your hand?
掌中停留？

81
00:12:41,794 --> 00:12:45,286
When I'm with her I'm confused Out of focus and bemused
当我和她同处就糊涂

82
00:12:45,531 --> 00:12:48,989
And I never know exactly where I am
茫然不知身在何处

83
00:12:49,201 --> 00:12:52,534
- Unpredictable as weather - She's as flighty as a feather
-如天气难测 -像羽毛飘忽

84
00:12:52,905 --> 00:12:54,702
- She's a darling - She's a demon
-她很可人 -她是恶魔

85
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:56,305
She's a lamb
她是羔羊

86
00:12:56,675 --> 00:13:00,304
She'll out pester any pest Drive a hornet from its nest
她让瘟神烦恼，把黄蜂赶出巢

87
00:13:00,546 --> 00:13:03,845
She can throw a whirling dervish Out of whirl
她能使僧侣昏头转向

88
00:13:04,416 --> 00:13:07,977
- She is gentle, she is wild - She's a riddle, she's a child
-她本性善良却又狂野 -她是迷一般的孩子

89
00:13:08,521 --> 00:13:11,115
- She's a headache - She's an angel
-她令人头痛 -她是天使

90
00:13:11,323 --> 00:13:15,180
She's a girl
她只是个女孩

91
00:13:15,995 --> 00:13:19,852
How do you solve a problem like Maria?
你要如何处理 像犸莉亚这样的问题人物？

92
00:13:20,065 --> 00:13:23,831
How do you catch a cloud And pin it down?
你要如何摘下浮云 然后钉牢？

93
00:13:24,069 --> 00:13:27,630
How do you find a word That means Maria?
你要如何用字眼来形容她？

94
00:13:27,873 --> 00:13:29,864
- A flibbertigibbet - A will-o'-the-wisp
-捣蛋鬼 -鬼灵精

95
00:13:30,075 --> 00:13:31,736
A clown
小丑

96
00:13:32,211 --> 00:13:35,977
Many a thing you know You'd like to tell her
许多事你觉得要告诉她

97
00:13:36,215 --> 00:13:39,673
Many a thing she ought to understand
许多事她应该明t

98
00:13:39,885 --> 00:13:44,242
- But how do you make her stay - And listen to all you say?
-但如何使她停下 -听你说完？

99
00:13:44,523 --> 00:13:48,584
How do you keep a wave upon the sand?
如何使海浪停留在沙滩上？

100
00:13:48,828 --> 00:13:54,653
How do you solve a problem like Maria?
你要如何处理 像犸莉亚这样的问题人物？

101
00:14:10,583 --> 00:14:17,375
How do you hold a moonbeam...
如何使月光在…

102
00:14:18,224 --> 00:14:24,686
...in your hand?
掌中停留？

103
00:14:36,542 --> 00:14:38,533
You may go in now, Maria.
你可以进去了，犸莉亚

104
00:14:51,056 --> 00:14:52,751
Come here, my child.
过来吧，孩子

105
00:14:59,265 --> 00:15:00,630
Now sit down.
坐下吧

106
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:05,128
Reverend Mother, I'm sorry. I couldn't help myself.
院长，我真抱歉 我只是无法自制

107
00:15:05,371 --> 00:15:08,295
- The hills were beckoning and before... - Dear.
-山峦在呼唤我… -亲爱的

108
00:15:08,774 --> 00:15:10,696
I haven't summoned you for apologies.
我不是要你来此道歉的

109
00:15:10,876 --> 00:15:13,174
Please let me ask for forgiveness.
请让我忏悔吧

110
00:15:13,846 --> 00:15:15,108
If you'll feel better.
如果会让你好过些的话

111
00:15:16,015 --> 00:15:18,506
Yes, you see, the sky was so blue today...
是的，今日的天空如此蔚蓝

112
00:15:18,651 --> 00:15:22,439
...and everything was so green and fragrant, I had to be a part of it.
万物如此碧绿芬芳 我必须成为其中一份子

113
00:15:22,688 --> 00:15:27,148
The Untersberg led me higher like it wanted me to go through the clouds.
安特斯让我愈爬愈高 好像要我跟它穿过云霄

114
00:15:27,359 --> 00:15:29,486
Suppose darkness had come and you were lost?
万一你在天黑时 迷路怎么办？

115
00:15:29,695 --> 00:15:32,027
Mother, I could never be lost up there.
院长，我绝对不会迷路的

116
00:15:32,197 --> 00:15:35,052
That's my mountain. I was brought up on it.
那是我的山，我在那儿长大的

117
00:15:35,234 --> 00:15:37,532
It was the mountain that led me to you.
就是那座山使我来找你的

118
00:15:38,337 --> 00:15:41,363
When I was a child, I would come down and climb a tree...
小时我常爬山

119
00:15:41,540 --> 00:15:43,337
...and look in your garden.
眺望你的花园

120
00:15:43,542 --> 00:15:46,500
I'd see the sisters at work and hear them sing.
看着修女们工作 听着她们晚祷的歌

121
00:15:47,846 --> 00:15:51,475
Which brings me to another transgression, Reverend Mother.
院长，我今天违反规定

122
00:15:51,684 --> 00:15:53,845
I was singing out there today.
未得准许唱歌

123
00:15:54,486 --> 00:15:58,513
Only in the abbey do we have rules about postulants singing.
在修道院只禁止见习修女唱歌

124
00:15:58,724 --> 00:16:00,715
I can't stop wherever I am.
不论在何处 我似乎都无法停止唱歌

125
00:16:00,993 --> 00:16:03,325
Worse, I can't seem to stop saying things.
更糟的是 我似乎也无法停止说话

126
00:16:03,562 --> 00:16:05,826
Everything I think and feel.
所有我想的和我的感觉

127
00:16:06,065 --> 00:16:07,555
Some call that "honesty."
有人会认为这是诚实

128
00:16:07,733 --> 00:16:10,122
Oh, but it's terrible, Reverend Mother!
但这是很糟糕的，院长

129
00:16:10,369 --> 00:16:14,226
You know how Sister Berthe makes me kiss the floor after a disagreement?
你知道贝诗修女总在争论之后 要我吻地板

130
00:16:14,573 --> 00:16:18,134
Lately, I kiss the floor when I see her coming to save time.
所以现在我看到她来就吻地板 以节省时间

131
00:16:20,779 --> 00:16:21,939
Maria...
犸莉亚

132
00:16:22,948 --> 00:16:25,940
...when you saw us over the wall and longed to be with us...
当你看到修道院的一切时 想要成为一员

133
00:16:26,218 --> 00:16:30,917
...that didn't mean you were prepared for the way we live here, did it?
那并不表示你已经准备好 要过这种生活方式，对不对？

134
00:16:32,257 --> 00:16:34,680
No, Mother, but I pray and I try.
不，院长 但我祷告，我努力尝试

135
00:16:34,893 --> 00:16:36,588
And I am learning. I really am.
我也在学习，我真的要做好

136
00:16:36,862 --> 00:16:39,524
What is the most important lesson you have learned here?
你在这里学到了 最重要的事是什么？

137
00:16:40,199 --> 00:16:43,965
To find out what is the will of God and do it wholeheartedly.
找出上帝的旨意 全心全意地侍奉主

138
00:16:46,805 --> 00:16:47,931
Maria...
犸莉亚

139
00:16:49,441 --> 00:16:52,239
...it seems to be God's will that you leave us.
似乎是上帝的意旨 你要离开我们

140
00:16:52,478 --> 00:16:53,968
- Leave? - Only for a while.
-离开？ -只是短暂的时间而已

141
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:56,812
No, Mother! Please don't send me away!
不，院长，别送我走

142
00:16:57,082 --> 00:17:01,314
This is where I belong. It's my home, my family. It's my life.
这里是我的家，我的家庭 我的生命

143
00:17:01,987 --> 00:17:04,979
- Are you truly ready for it? - Yes, I am.
-你真预备献身上帝？ -我是的

144
00:17:05,157 --> 00:17:10,117
If you go out into the world for a time, knowing what we expect of you...
或许如果你到外面去看看 就明白我们对你的期望

145
00:17:10,396 --> 00:17:13,126
...you will find out if you can expect it of yourself.
你就有机会找出 你对你自己的期望

146
00:17:13,332 --> 00:17:17,621
I know what you expect, Mother, and I can do it! I promise I can!
我知道你期望什么，院长 我相信我可以做得到

147
00:17:21,206 --> 00:17:22,434
Yes, Mother.
是的，院长

148
00:17:24,510 --> 00:17:26,205
If it is God's will.
如果是上帝的旨意

149
00:17:28,447 --> 00:17:33,510
There is a family near Salzburg that needs a governess until September.
萨尔斯堡有个家庭 需要家庭教师一直到九月

150
00:17:33,786 --> 00:17:35,981
- September? - For seven children.
-到九月？ -照料七个孩子

151
00:17:36,622 --> 00:17:37,646
Seven children?!
七个孩子？！

152
00:17:37,923 --> 00:17:39,151
Do you like children?
你喜欢孩子吗？

153
00:17:39,958 --> 00:17:41,755
Well, yes, but seven!
是的，但七个…

154
00:17:42,928 --> 00:17:46,091
I will tell Captain von Trapp to expect you tomorrow.
我会告诉范崔普舰长 你明天去

155
00:17:46,632 --> 00:17:47,963
Captain?
舰长？

156
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:53,524
A retired officer of the Imperial Navy. A fine man and a brave one.
他是皇家海军的退役军官 人很好又很勇敢

157
00:17:53,806 --> 00:17:56,502
His wife died, and he is alone with the children.
他太太数年前去世 留下那些孩子给他

158
00:17:56,675 --> 00:18:00,998
I understand he has had a difficult time keeping a governess there.
我明白他要留住那些家庭教师 会有些困难

159
00:18:01,814 --> 00:18:04,112
Why difficult, Reverend Mother?
为何会有困难，院长？

160
00:18:05,484 --> 00:18:08,373
The Lord will show you in His own good time.
在适当的时机 上帝会让你明白的

161
00:18:45,224 --> 00:18:47,715
When the Lord closes a door...
当主关上门时

162
00:18:47,926 --> 00:18:50,417
...somewhere He opens a window.
他会在某处打开窗子的

163
00:18:52,831 --> 00:18:57,791
What will this day be like?
这天会是如何？

164
00:18:58,036 --> 00:19:00,231
I wonder
我怀疑

165
00:19:06,745 --> 00:19:10,875
What will my future be?
我的未来呢？

166
00:19:11,717 --> 00:19:13,947
I wonder
我怀疑

167
00:19:15,554 --> 00:19:18,580
It could be so exciting
外边的自由逍遥世界

168
00:19:18,824 --> 00:19:21,918
To be out in the world To be free
应该令人兴奋

169
00:19:22,127 --> 00:19:25,221
My heart should be wildly rejoicing
我的心该狂欢愉悦

170
00:19:26,398 --> 00:19:31,722
Oh, what's the matter with me?
我到底是怎么回事？

171
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:35,098
I've always longed for adventure
我一向渴望着冒险

172
00:19:35,374 --> 00:19:38,935
To do the things I've never dared
做我不敢做的事

173
00:19:39,211 --> 00:19:42,408
Now here I'm facing adventure
现在我面对着冒险

174
00:19:42,648 --> 00:19:48,780
Then why am I so scared?
为何我如此害怕？

175
00:19:52,257 --> 00:19:55,112
A captain with seven children
一位舰长和七位孩子

176
00:19:55,394 --> 00:19:58,227
What's so fearsome about that?
有何可怕？

177
00:20:00,766 --> 00:20:03,360
I must stop these doubts and worries
我必须停止多疑和忧虑

178
00:20:03,602 --> 00:20:06,457
If I don't I just know I'll turn back
不然，我会回到原点

179
00:20:06,738 --> 00:20:09,901
I must dream of the things I am seeking
我必须梦想我所追求的事物

180
00:20:10,943 --> 00:20:15,937
I am seeking the courage I lack
我在追求我所欠缺的勇气

181
00:20:16,848 --> 00:20:20,739
The courage to serve them With reliance
有勇气信赖他们

182
00:20:20,986 --> 00:20:23,910
Face my mistakes without defiance
虚心面对我的错误

183
00:20:24,156 --> 00:20:25,885
Show them I'm worthy
让他们知道我的好处

184
00:20:26,124 --> 00:20:28,786
And while I show them
同时也让自己看见

185
00:20:29,027 --> 00:20:32,815
I'll show me
自己的好处

186
00:20:33,031 --> 00:20:38,458
So let them bring on All their problems
让他们提出他们的问题

187
00:20:38,670 --> 00:20:41,935
I'll do better than my best
我会做得比最好还要更好

188
00:20:42,174 --> 00:20:45,268
I have confidence They'll put me to the test
我有信心，让他们来考验我吧

189
00:20:45,510 --> 00:20:48,968
But I'll make them see I have confidence in me
我会让他们明白，我充满信心

190
00:20:49,181 --> 00:20:52,480
Somehow I will impress them
我要使他们印象深刻

191
00:20:52,718 --> 00:20:55,983
I will be firm but kind
我会坚决而和善

192
00:20:56,221 --> 00:20:59,520
And all those children Heaven bless them
上苍祝福那些孩子们

193
00:20:59,791 --> 00:21:03,056
They will look up to me And mind me
他们会以我为榜样，听我的话

194
00:21:03,228 --> 00:21:06,459
With each step I am more certain
每走一步，我更确信

195
00:21:06,698 --> 00:21:09,963
Everything will turn out fine
一切事情都会好转

196
00:21:10,168 --> 00:21:13,296
I have confidence The world can all be mine
我有信心世界会由我掌握

197
00:21:13,505 --> 00:21:19,000
They'll have to agree I have confidence in me
因为我对自己有信心

198
00:21:20,512 --> 00:21:23,310
I have confidence in sunshine
我对阳光有信心

199
00:21:23,548 --> 00:21:26,642
I have confidence in rain
我对雨水有信心

200
00:21:26,852 --> 00:21:29,741
I have confidence That spring will come again
我深信春天会再来

201
00:21:30,022 --> 00:21:33,082
Besides which you see I have confidence in me
我对自己更有信心

202
00:21:33,358 --> 00:21:36,486
Strength doesn't lie in numbers
力量不存在于数字里

203
00:21:36,728 --> 00:21:39,754
Strength doesn't lie in wealth
力量不存在于财富中

204
00:21:40,032 --> 00:21:43,331
Strength lies in nights Of peaceful slumbers
力量存在于静夜的酣睡中

205
00:21:43,568 --> 00:21:46,492
When you wake up, wake up It's healthy
当你醒来就充满精神

206
00:21:46,738 --> 00:21:49,764
All I trust I leave my heart to
我信任心中的指引

207
00:21:50,008 --> 00:21:52,897
All I trust becomes my own
就会成为我的

208
00:21:53,111 --> 00:21:57,901
I have confidence in confidence alone
我对信心更有信心

209
00:22:12,564 --> 00:22:14,191
Oh, help.
救命

210
00:22:26,378 --> 00:22:33,034
I have confidence in confidence alone
我对信心更有信心

211
00:22:33,785 --> 00:22:38,609
Besides which you see I have confidence...
况且，你看，我对自己…

212
00:22:38,890 --> 00:22:45,250
...in me
充满信心！

213
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:54,636
Hello. Here I am.
你好，我来了

214
00:22:57,142 --> 00:22:59,303
I'm from the convent. I'm the new governess, captain.
我从修道院来的 我是新的家教，舰长

215
00:23:00,979 --> 00:23:04,244
And I'm the old butler, fraulein.
而我是老管家，小姐

216
00:23:06,151 --> 00:23:07,982
Well, how do you do?
你好

217
00:23:18,497 --> 00:23:22,593
You'll wait here, please.
请你在此稍候

218
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:53,050
In future, remember certain rooms in this house are not to be disturbed.
以后请记住 这里有些房间是不能乱闯的

219
00:24:54,192 --> 00:24:55,682
Yes, captain, sir.
是的，舰长，先生

220
00:25:03,568 --> 00:25:08,801
- Why do you stare at me that way? - You don't look like a sea captain.
-你为何如此看着我？ -你看起来一点都不像海上的舰长

221
00:25:10,075 --> 00:25:13,101
I'm afraid you don't look very much like a governess.
我也认为 你一点都不像个家庭教师

222
00:25:13,678 --> 00:25:14,906
- Turn around. - What?
-请转身 -什么？

223
00:25:15,113 --> 00:25:16,444
Turn.
转身

224
00:25:19,684 --> 00:25:20,946
Hat off.
拿下帽子

225
00:25:24,055 --> 00:25:26,683
Put on another dress before meeting the children.
你和孩子见面前 最好先换衣服

226
00:25:26,925 --> 00:25:28,552
But I don't have another.
但我没有衣服换了

227
00:25:28,793 --> 00:25:31,682
When we enter the abbey, our worldly clothes go to the poor.
我进入修道院时 将所有衣服送给穷人了

228
00:25:31,930 --> 00:25:33,124
What about this one?
这一件呢？

229
00:25:33,398 --> 00:25:34,729
The poor didn't want it.
穷人不要这一件

230
00:25:36,568 --> 00:25:40,060
There wasn't time to make a new dress. I can make clothes.
我本想为自己做新衣服的 但时间不够，我会自己做衣服

231
00:25:41,306 --> 00:25:43,570
I'll see that you get some material.
我会确定你有一些布料的

232
00:25:44,276 --> 00:25:45,834
Today, if possible.
今天，如果可能的话

233
00:25:46,845 --> 00:25:48,608
- Now, fraulein... - Maria.
-现在…小姐 -莉亚

234
00:25:48,847 --> 00:25:51,509
I don't know how much the abbess told you.
我不知道院长告诉了你多少

235
00:25:51,783 --> 00:25:54,411
You are the twelfth governess...
在许多家教中你是第12位了

236
00:25:54,619 --> 00:25:57,042
...to look after my children since their mother died.
自从他们的母亲去世后 来此照料他们

237
00:25:57,222 --> 00:25:59,486
I trust you will be an improvement on the last one.
我相信你会比上一个更好

238
00:25:59,758 --> 00:26:01,589
She stayed only two hours.
她只停留了两小时

239
00:26:03,295 --> 00:26:05,855
What's wrong with the children, sir?
孩子们有何不对吗？

240
00:26:07,332 --> 00:26:11,689
Nothing is wrong with the children, only the governesses.
孩子们都很正常 是家庭教师的错

241
00:26:11,870 --> 00:26:16,933
They could not maintain discipline, without which the house cannot be run.
她们完全无法维持纪律 没有纪律就不能管好这个家

242
00:26:17,842 --> 00:26:19,764
Drill them in their studies.
你得督促孩子学习

243
00:26:19,945 --> 00:26:23,437
I will not permit them to dream away their summer holidays.
我不准他们虚度假期

244
00:26:23,682 --> 00:26:26,344
Each afternoon, they march, breathing deeply.
下午他们要在庭院操练

245
00:26:26,618 --> 00:26:28,210
Bedtime is to be strictly observed.
还要严守就时间

246
00:26:28,386 --> 00:26:29,444
When do they play?
请问他们何时玩耍？

247
00:26:29,654 --> 00:26:33,784
You will see to it that they conduct themselves with the utmost decorum.
你要看着他们 确定他们循规蹈矩

248
00:26:33,959 --> 00:26:36,883
- I am placing you in command. - Yes, sir.
-我要你负责这一切 -是的，先生

249
00:27:57,542 --> 00:27:58,702
Now...
现在…

250
00:27:59,277 --> 00:28:02,235
...this is your new governess, Fraulein Maria.
这位是你们的新家教 犸莉亚小姐

251
00:28:03,915 --> 00:28:05,906
Give your name at your signal.
当我吹你们的讯号时 你们踏前一步报出名字

252
00:28:06,117 --> 00:28:10,281
Fraulein, listen carefully. Learn their signals so you can call them.
而你要仔细注意那讯号 以便日后召唤他们

253
00:28:11,589 --> 00:28:12,988
Liesl.
莉莎

254
00:28:13,258 --> 00:28:14,987
Friedrich.
费瑞克

255
00:28:15,260 --> 00:28:16,784
Louisa.
露易莎

256
00:28:17,062 --> 00:28:18,359
Kurt.
寇特

257
00:28:18,563 --> 00:28:19,587
Brigitta.
碧姬塔

258
00:28:19,864 --> 00:28:21,126
Marta.
犸塔

259
00:28:27,505 --> 00:28:28,870
Gretl.
葛特儿

260
00:28:33,478 --> 00:28:36,902
Now, let's see how well you listened.
现在看看你的耳力如何

261
00:28:37,148 --> 00:28:39,514
I won't need to whistle for them, Reverend Captain.
我想我不用哨子的，舰长

262
00:28:39,784 --> 00:28:43,242
I mean, I'll use their names. Such lovely names.
我会叫他们的名字 尤其是有如此美的名字

263
00:28:43,455 --> 00:28:46,618
Fraulein, this is a large house. The grounds are extensive.
小姐，这是座大房子 地方很宽广

264
00:28:46,891 --> 00:28:49,553
And I will not have anyone shouting.
而我不容许任何人在此喊叫

265
00:28:49,728 --> 00:28:51,650
You will take this, please. Learn to use it.
请你拿这个，学习使用它

266
00:28:51,830 --> 00:28:53,457
The children will help you.
孩子们也会帮你的

267
00:28:55,500 --> 00:28:59,493
Now, when I want you, this is what you will hear.
我要找你，你会听到这个讯号

268
00:29:00,338 --> 00:29:02,203
Oh, no, sir. I'm sorry, sir!
不，很抱歉，先生

269
00:29:03,007 --> 00:29:04,634
I could never answer to a whistle.
我绝不会听哨子回报的

270
00:29:04,809 --> 00:29:07,437
Whistles are for animals, not for children.
哨子是用来召唤动物的 但绝不是对孩子

271
00:29:07,679 --> 00:29:09,704
And definitely not for me.
而且绝对不会是我

272
00:29:09,981 --> 00:29:12,643
It would be too humiliating.
这是种很大的侮辱

273
00:29:13,451 --> 00:29:18,707
Fraulein, were you this much trouble at the abbey?
小姐，你在修道院 也是如此麻烦的吗？

274
00:29:18,890 --> 00:29:20,152
Oh, much more, sir.
麻烦得多，先生

275
00:29:31,169 --> 00:29:32,796
I don't know your signal.
我不知道你的讯号

276
00:29:34,205 --> 00:29:36,833
You may call me "captain."
你可以叫我舰长

277
00:29:49,754 --> 00:29:51,244
At ease.
稍息

278
00:29:54,025 --> 00:29:55,583
Now that there's just us...
现在只剩下我们

279
00:29:55,827 --> 00:29:59,991
...would you please tell me all your names again and how old you are.
请再一次告诉我你们的名字 还有你们的年龄

280
00:30:00,498 --> 00:30:04,491
I'm Liesl. I'm 16 years old, and I don't need a governess.
我叫莉莎，我16岁 我不需要家教

281
00:30:05,236 --> 00:30:08,399
I'm glad you told me, Liesl. We'll just be good friends.
莉莎，很高兴你告诉我 我们可以做好朋友

282
00:30:10,475 --> 00:30:14,366
I'm Friedrich. I'm 14. I'm impossible.
我叫费瑞克，我14岁 我是朽木

283
00:30:14,546 --> 00:30:16,309
Really? Who told you that, Friedrich?
真的？谁告诉你的，费瑞克？

284
00:30:16,481 --> 00:30:20,008
Fraulein Josephine. Four governesses ago.
约瑟芬小姐，前四任教师

285
00:30:20,418 --> 00:30:21,908
I'm Brigitta.
我叫碧姬塔

286
00:30:23,721 --> 00:30:27,714
You didn't tell me how old you are, Louisa.
你没告诉我你多大，露易莎

287
00:30:28,426 --> 00:30:30,690
I'm Brigitta. She's Louisa.
我叫碧姬塔，她叫露易莎

288
00:30:30,929 --> 00:30:33,693
She's 13 years old, and you're smart.
她13岁，而你很聪明

289
00:30:33,932 --> 00:30:37,754
I'm 10, and I think your dress is the ugliest one I ever saw.
我10岁，而我认为你的衣服 是我见过最丑的

290
00:30:37,936 --> 00:30:40,598
- Brigitta, you shouldn't say that. - Why not?
-碧姬塔，你不该这样说的 -为何？

291
00:30:40,805 --> 00:30:43,103
- Don't you think it's ugly? - Of course.
-你不认为很丑？ -当然

292
00:30:43,374 --> 00:30:46,070
But Fraulein Helga's was ugliest.
但赫德小姐才是最丑的

293
00:30:46,311 --> 00:30:48,939
I'm Kurt. I'm 11. I'm incorrigible.
我是寇特，11岁，我很任性

294
00:30:49,214 --> 00:30:52,308
- Congratulations. - What's "incorrigible"?
-恭喜你！ -什么是任性？

295
00:30:52,584 --> 00:30:56,441
I think it means you want to be treated like a boy.
那表示你希望 被人当作是小男孩

296
00:30:58,623 --> 00:31:01,922
I'm Marta, and I'm going to be seven on Tuesday.
我是犸塔，星期二我就7岁了

297
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:03,650
I'd like a pink parasol.
我爱粉红色阳伞

298
00:31:04,762 --> 00:31:06,423
Pink's my favorite color too.
纷红色也是我的颜色

299
00:31:08,633 --> 00:31:09,895
Yes, you're Gretl.
是的，你是葛特儿

300
00:31:10,735 --> 00:31:12,600
And you're five years old?
而你已经5岁了？

301
00:31:12,904 --> 00:31:14,895
My, you're practically a lady.
天啊，你几乎快成为淑女了

302
00:31:17,408 --> 00:31:20,502
I have to tell you a secret. I've never been a governess.
现在我要告诉你们一个秘密 我从未当过家庭教师

303
00:31:21,980 --> 00:31:24,710
You don't know anything about being a governess?
你一点也不懂如何当家庭教师？

304
00:31:24,883 --> 00:31:26,373
Nothing. I'll need lots of advice.
一点也不懂，我需要许多建议

305
00:31:27,318 --> 00:31:31,948
The best way to start is to tell Father to mind his own business.
首先，就是告诉父亲 要他少管闲事

306
00:31:32,123 --> 00:31:33,920
Never come to dinner on time.
你绝对不能准时来用餐

307
00:31:34,125 --> 00:31:36,423
Never eat your soup quietly.
喝汤也不要太小声

308
00:31:37,128 --> 00:31:39,153
During dessert, always blow your nose.
吃甜点时，要擤鼻子

309
00:31:39,430 --> 00:31:42,160
Don't you believe a word they say, Fraulein Maria.
别听他们说的话，犸莉亚小姐

310
00:31:42,433 --> 00:31:45,789
- Oh, why not? - Because I like you.
-为什么？ -因为我喜欢你

311
00:31:46,537 --> 00:31:48,562
Children, outside for your walk.
孩子们，出去散步

312
00:31:48,806 --> 00:31:50,637
Father's orders. Hurry up.
父亲的命令，快点

313
00:31:50,875 --> 00:31:52,172
Quick, quick, quick.
快…

314
00:31:52,443 --> 00:31:55,640
Fraulein Maria, I'm Frau Schmidt, the housekeeper.
犸莉亚小姐 我是蒙思蜜德，女管家

315
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:56,972
How do you do.
你好

316
00:31:57,148 --> 00:31:59,981
I'll show you to your room. Follow me.
我带你去房间，跟我来

317
00:32:11,129 --> 00:32:12,858
Poor little dears.
可怜的小东西

318
00:32:25,610 --> 00:32:29,899
You're very lucky. With Fraulein Helga it was a snake.
你运气很好 赫德小姐拿到的是条蛇

319
00:32:43,861 --> 00:32:45,158
Good evening.
晚安

320
00:32:46,564 --> 00:32:50,159
- Good evening, children. - Good evening, Fraulein Maria.
-晚安，孩子们 -晚安，犸莉亚小姐

321
00:32:57,342 --> 00:32:59,003
Enchanting little ritual.
很独特的举止

322
00:32:59,210 --> 00:33:01,906
Something you learned at the abbey?
是在修道院学来的吗？

323
00:33:03,147 --> 00:33:05,411
No.
不

324
00:33:07,085 --> 00:33:08,382
Rheumatism.
是风湿

325
00:33:18,162 --> 00:33:21,290
Excuse me, captain. Haven't we forgotten to thank the Lord?
对不起，舰长 我们是否忘了向主祷告？

326
00:33:29,540 --> 00:33:32,532
For what we receive, may the Lord make us truly thankful.
感谢上帝赐给我们一切

327
00:33:33,077 --> 00:33:34,965
- Amen. - Amen.
-阿门 -阿门

328
00:33:39,550 --> 00:33:41,506
I'd like to thank you all...
我要感谢各位

329
00:33:41,686 --> 00:33:44,678
...for the precious gift you left in my pocket today.
今天放在我口袋中的珍贵礼物

330
00:33:48,126 --> 00:33:49,957
What gift?
是什么礼物？

331
00:33:53,097 --> 00:33:55,258
It's a secret between the children and me.
这是我和孩子们之间的秘密

332
00:33:55,466 --> 00:33:59,129
Then I suggest you keep it, and let us eat.
那我建议你就留着 让我们可以吃饭

333
00:33:59,504 --> 00:34:01,460
Knowing how nervous I must have been...
我了解陌生人在新家庭里

334
00:34:01,739 --> 00:34:04,128
...a stranger in a new household...
会是有多么紧张

335
00:34:04,342 --> 00:34:07,436
...knowing how important it was for me to feel accepted...
了解能被接受 会是多么重要的事

336
00:34:07,712 --> 00:34:11,876
...it was so kind and thoughtful of you to make my first moments here...
你们使我感到多么温暖

337
00:34:12,050 --> 00:34:14,314
...so warm and happy...
快乐和…

338
00:34:14,585 --> 00:34:16,314
...and pleasant.
欢悦

339
00:34:25,596 --> 00:34:27,621
- What is the matter, Marta? - Nothing.
-犸塔，你怎么了？ -没事

340
00:34:40,011 --> 00:34:41,069
Fraulein...
小姐

341
00:34:41,245 --> 00:34:45,136
...is it to be at every meal or merely at dinnertime...
是不是每餐饭

342
00:34:45,349 --> 00:34:49,945
...that you intend leading us through this rare and wonderful new world...
你都想要让我们

343
00:34:50,154 --> 00:34:51,815
...of indigestion?
消化不良？

344
00:34:53,357 --> 00:34:56,190
They're all right, captain. They're just happy.
不，舰长，他们只是很高兴

345
00:35:14,979 --> 00:35:17,675
- Rolfe, good evening. - Good evening, Franz.
-劳夫，晚安 -晚安，福兰斯

346
00:35:17,915 --> 00:35:20,679
- I trust everything is under control? - Yes, yes.
-一切正常吗？ -是的

347
00:35:22,286 --> 00:35:24,709
- Are there any developments? - Perhaps.
-有何进展吗？ -或许

348
00:35:24,922 --> 00:35:27,083
- Is the captain home? - He's at dinner.
-舰长在不在？ -他在用晚餐

349
00:35:27,358 --> 00:35:29,690
- With the family? - Yes.
-和他的家人？ -是的

350
00:35:29,927 --> 00:35:31,690
Give him this telegram at once.
请立刻把电报交给他

351
00:35:32,497 --> 00:35:33,521
Certainly.
没问题

352
00:35:45,209 --> 00:35:46,938
A telegram for you, sir.
您的电报，先生

353
00:35:49,814 --> 00:35:51,611
Franz? Who delivered it?
福兰斯，谁送来的？

354
00:35:51,916 --> 00:35:53,941
That young lad Rolfe, of course.
当然是劳夫了

355
00:35:56,220 --> 00:35:57,949
Father, may I be excused?
父亲，我能先告退吗？

356
00:35:58,923 --> 00:36:03,451
Children, in the morning I shall be going to Vienna.
孩子们，明早我必须去维也纳

357
00:36:03,628 --> 00:36:06,119
Not again, Father!
怎么又来了，父亲？

358
00:36:10,034 --> 00:36:12,127
How long will you be gone this time?
这次你要去多久，父亲？

359
00:36:12,837 --> 00:36:14,236
I'm not sure, Gretl.
我不确定，葛特儿

360
00:36:14,472 --> 00:36:18,067
- To visit Baroness Schraeder again? - Mind your own business!
-是不是去看史蕾特男爵夫人？ -少管闲事

361
00:36:19,043 --> 00:36:20,931
As a matter of fact, yes, Louisa.
事实上，是的，露易莎

362
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:26,571
- Why can't we ever see the baroness? - Why would she want to see you?
-为何我们总见不到男爵夫人呢？ -为何她要见你？

363
00:36:26,851 --> 00:36:31,743
You are going to see the baroness. I'm bringing her back with me to visit.
你会见到她的 我要带她回来这里，和大家认识

364
00:36:33,257 --> 00:36:34,986
And Uncle Max.
还有麦斯伯伯

365
00:36:35,259 --> 00:36:37,750
Uncle Max!
麦伯伯

366
00:36:53,778 --> 00:36:55,075
Rolfe!
劳夫

367
00:36:58,149 --> 00:36:59,173
Oh, Rolfe!
哦，劳夫

368
00:37:01,786 --> 00:37:04,675
- No, Liesl. We mustn't! - Why not, silly?
-不，莉莎，我们不能 -为何，傻瓜？

369
00:37:04,956 --> 00:37:07,584
- I don't know... - Isn't this why you're waiting?
-我不知道 -你在此不是为了等我吗？

370
00:37:07,825 --> 00:37:09,656
Yes, of course.
是的，当然

371
00:37:09,927 --> 00:37:12,691
- I've missed you, Liesl. - You have? How much?
-我想你，莉莎 -有吗，有多想？

372
00:37:12,964 --> 00:37:16,786
I even thought of sending a telegram, so I'd be able to deliver it here.
好多，我甚至想给你送电报 让我好来此地

373
00:37:17,034 --> 00:37:20,925
Oh, that's a lovely thought! Why don't you, right now?
那是很美好的想法 你为何不做呢？就现在吧

374
00:37:21,172 --> 00:37:25,336
- But I'm here! - Please, Rolfe. Send me a telegram.
-但是我就在此啊 -拜托，劳夫，送给我电报吧

375
00:37:25,610 --> 00:37:29,034
I'll start it for you. "Dear Liesl..."
我为你起稿：“亲爱的莉莎…”

376
00:37:29,714 --> 00:37:33,343
"Dear Liesl: I'd like to be able to tell you...
亲爱的莉莎 我很想要告诉你…

377
00:37:33,551 --> 00:37:35,781
...how I feel about you. Stop.
我对你的感觉，完结

378
00:37:36,020 --> 00:37:40,548
Unfortunately, this wire is already too expensive.
很不幸，电报费用太贵了

379
00:37:40,791 --> 00:37:42,190
Sincerely, Rolfe."
真挚的劳夫

380
00:37:42,426 --> 00:37:45,156
- "Sincerely"? - Cordially.
-真挚？ -衷心的

381
00:37:45,363 --> 00:37:48,025
- "Cordially"? - Affectionately?
-衷心的？ -深情的？

382
00:37:50,368 --> 00:37:52,427
Will there be any reply?
会不会有回电？

383
00:37:53,704 --> 00:37:55,865
"Dear Rolfe: Stop.
亲爱的劳夫，完结

384
00:37:56,874 --> 00:38:00,002
Don't stop! Your Liesl."
不要完结，你的莉莎

385
00:38:01,679 --> 00:38:05,536
If only we didn't have to wait for someone to send Father a telegram.
如果我们不用等别人 给父亲打电报才能见面就好了

386
00:38:05,816 --> 00:38:08,205
How do I know when I'll see you again?
我如何知道何时才能见到你？

387
00:38:09,086 --> 00:38:10,348
Well, let's see...
让我想想看

388
00:38:13,357 --> 00:38:15,245
I could come here by mistake.
我可以因为搞错而来

389
00:38:16,260 --> 00:38:20,959
With a telegram for Colonel Schneider! He's here from Berlin staying with...
要给史奈德上校电报 他从柏林来此，停留在…

390
00:38:21,866 --> 00:38:25,165
No one knows he's here. Don't tell your father.
没有人知道他在此的 别告诉你父亲

391
00:38:25,403 --> 00:38:28,566
- Why not? - Your father's so Austrian.
-为何不？ -因为你父亲自视为奥地利人

392
00:38:28,773 --> 00:38:30,070
We're all Austrian.
我们都是奥地利人

393
00:38:30,274 --> 00:38:34,699
Some think we ought to be German, and they're very mad at those who don't.
而那些认为该自视为德国人的 他们不希望这样

394
00:38:34,912 --> 00:38:36,709
They're getting ready to...
他们已准备好…

395
00:38:38,382 --> 00:38:40,771
Let's hope your father doesn't get into trouble.
我希望你父亲不会惹上麻烦

396
00:38:41,052 --> 00:38:46,012
Don't worry. He's a big naval hero. He was even decorated by the emperor.
别担心父亲，他是海军大英雄 他甚至由国王亲自授动

397
00:38:46,223 --> 00:38:49,488
I don't worry about him. I worry about his daughter.
我不担心他 但我却担心他的女儿

398
00:38:50,027 --> 00:38:51,221
Me? Why?
我？为什么？

399
00:38:51,395 --> 00:38:52,384
- Well, you're so... - What?
-你是那样… -什么？

400
00:38:53,780 --> 00:38:55,489
You're such a baby!
你是如此地年轻

401
00:38:55,700 --> 00:38:58,589
I'm 16. What's such a baby about that?
我16岁了，一点都不年轻了

402
00:39:00,871 --> 00:39:04,363
You wait, little girl On an empty stage
小女孩在空虚的舞台等待

403
00:39:04,608 --> 00:39:07,998
For fate to turn the light on
等待命运的开始

404
00:39:08,612 --> 00:39:11,877
Your life, little girl Is an empty page
你的生命目前是空白的一页

405
00:39:12,116 --> 00:39:16,212
That men will want to write on
男人希望在上面书写

406
00:39:16,921 --> 00:39:22,416
To write on
书写

407
00:39:23,327 --> 00:39:27,252
You are 16 going on 17
你16岁，快17岁了

408
00:39:27,465 --> 00:39:31,253
Baby, it's time to think
宝贝，该去思考了

409
00:39:31,469 --> 00:39:35,132
Better beware Be canny and careful
应当警觉，谨慎和当心

410
00:39:35,406 --> 00:39:39,035
Baby, you're on the brink
宝贝，你正在边缘

411
00:39:39,343 --> 00:39:43,165
You are 16 going on 17
你是16岁，快17岁

412
00:39:43,414 --> 00:39:47,043
Fellows will fall in line
男孩们会排队等候

413
00:39:47,351 --> 00:39:50,684
Eager young lads And roues and cads
很积极的年轻人 和一些鲁莽小人

414
00:39:50,921 --> 00:39:54,812
Will offer you food and wine
会向你献酒和美食

415
00:39:55,092 --> 00:39:58,858
Totally unprepared are you
你完全没有心理准备

416
00:39:59,296 --> 00:40:02,823
To face a world of men
去面对男人的世界

417
00:40:03,434 --> 00:40:07,598
Timid and shy and scared are you
怯懦和害羞，你会如此的畏惧

418
00:40:07,838 --> 00:40:11,365
Of things beyond your ken
事情全在你知识范围以外

419
00:40:11,609 --> 00:40:15,466
You need someone older and wiser
你需要一位成熟和有智慧的人

420
00:40:15,679 --> 00:40:19,570
Telling you what to do
告诉你怎么做

421
00:40:19,817 --> 00:40:23,207
I am 17 going on 18
我17岁快18岁了

422
00:40:23,487 --> 00:40:29,448
I'll take care of you
我能够照顾你

423
00:41:01,926 --> 00:41:05,316
I am 16 going on 17
我16岁快17岁了

424
00:41:05,529 --> 00:41:08,885
I know that I'm naive
我知道我很天真

425
00:41:09,166 --> 00:41:12,397
Fellows I meet May tell me I'm sweet
我遇上的男孩或会说我很甜美

426
00:41:12,636 --> 00:41:16,367
And willingly I believe
我会心甘情愿地相信

427
00:41:16,774 --> 00:41:19,937
I am 16 going on 17
我16岁快17岁了

428
00:41:20,244 --> 00:41:23,941
Innocent as a rose
如玫瑰般无邪

429
00:41:24,181 --> 00:41:27,639
Bachelor dandies Drinkers of brandies
那些喝着白兰地的单身男子

430
00:41:27,885 --> 00:41:31,218
What do I know of those?
我对此毫无认识

431
00:41:31,455 --> 00:41:35,016
Totally unprepared am I
完全没有心理准备

432
00:41:35,226 --> 00:41:38,718
To face a world of men
去面对男人的世界

433
00:41:39,196 --> 00:41:42,461
Timid and shy and scared am I
我是如此怯懦，害羞和害怕

434
00:41:42,733 --> 00:41:46,430
Of things beyond my ken
事情全在我知识范围以外

435
00:41:46,904 --> 00:41:50,465
I need someone older and wiser
我需要一位成熟和有智慧的人

436
00:41:50,741 --> 00:41:54,040
Telling me what to do
告诉我怎么做

437
00:41:54,411 --> 00:41:58,074
You are 17 going on 18
你17岁快18岁了

438
00:41:58,282 --> 00:42:03,948
I'll depend on you
我会完全信赖你

439
00:43:57,034 --> 00:43:58,399
Come in.
请进

440
00:43:59,436 --> 00:44:01,097
Frau Schmidt.
思蜜德小姐

441
00:44:03,407 --> 00:44:05,204
For your new dresses.
这是给你做新衣服的

442
00:44:05,442 --> 00:44:09,503
- The captain had these sent from town. - Oh, how lovely!
-舰长从城里买来的 -多么美的布料

443
00:44:09,747 --> 00:44:13,205
These will make the prettiest clothes I've ever had.
我可以缝制出最漂亮的衣裳

444
00:44:13,450 --> 00:44:16,942
Do you think he would get me more material if I asked?
告诉我，如果我再要求 多点布料的话，他会肯吗？

445
00:44:17,221 --> 00:44:20,850
- How many dresses do you need? - Not for me, for the children.
-家庭教师需要多少衣服？ -不是为我，是为了孩子

446
00:44:21,091 --> 00:44:23,184
I want to make them some play clothes.
我要为他们做点游戏服

447
00:44:23,394 --> 00:44:26,955
The von Trapp children don't play. They march.
范崔普的孩子不玩游戏 他们只做操练

448
00:44:27,431 --> 00:44:29,922
Surely you don't approve of that.
所以你不赞成了

449
00:44:30,901 --> 00:44:33,267
Ever since the captain lost his poor wife...
自从舰长失去他太太后

450
00:44:33,537 --> 00:44:36,233
...he runs this house as if on one of his ships.
他管理家事就好像管军舰般

451
00:44:37,074 --> 00:44:38,439
Whistles, orders.
哨音、命令

452
00:44:38,709 --> 00:44:40,574
No more music, no more laughing.
再也没有音乐 没有欢笑了

453
00:44:40,844 --> 00:44:44,234
Nothing that reminds him of her. Even the children.
不愿接触任何能让他 想起她的事物，孩子们也一样

454
00:44:44,882 --> 00:44:45,940
But that's so wrong.
那太不对了

455
00:44:46,784 --> 00:44:48,274
Oh, well.
可以怎样？

456
00:44:48,552 --> 00:44:52,215
How do you like your room? There'll be new drapes at the windows.
你喜欢你的房间吗？ 你会有新的窗帘

457
00:44:52,456 --> 00:44:53,787
Bu these are fine.
它们还好好地

458
00:44:53,957 --> 00:44:55,584
New ones have been ordered.
反正新的已经订了

459
00:44:55,793 --> 00:44:59,126
- But I really don't need them. - Good night, now.
-我真的不需要它们 -晚安

460
00:44:59,396 --> 00:45:03,423
Frau Schmidt, if I asked the captain about the material?
思蜜德小姐，你想如果明天 我要求他布料的事

461
00:45:03,667 --> 00:45:08,058
- He's leaving in the morning. - Of course. How long will he be gone?
-他明早就离开去维也纳 -是，他要去多久呢？

462
00:45:08,739 --> 00:45:13,301
It depends. The last time he visited the baroness, he stayed for a month.
那得看情况，上次他在男爵夫人 那儿停留了一个月

463
00:45:14,478 --> 00:45:19,074
I shouldn't be saying this to you. I don't know you that well.
我本不该说这些的 我们还不很熟悉

464
00:45:19,316 --> 00:45:22,240
But if you ask me, the captain's thinking seriously...
但如果你问我的话 舰长是很认真地…

465
00:45:22,453 --> 00:45:24,683
...of marrying her before summer's over.
想娶这女人

466
00:45:24,922 --> 00:45:28,153
Wonderful! The children will have a mother again.
那太好了 孩子们会有新母亲了

467
00:45:29,626 --> 00:45:30,923
Yes.
是的

468
00:45:31,161 --> 00:45:32,924
Well, good night.
晚安

469
00:45:33,130 --> 00:45:34,529
Good night.
晚安

470
00:45:52,916 --> 00:45:55,771
Dear Father, now I know why You sent me here.
亲爱的天父 我现在知道为何你要我来此了

471
00:45:55,986 --> 00:45:58,841
To help these children prepare for a new mother.
是帮助这些孩子 准备接受他们的新母亲

472
00:45:59,123 --> 00:46:02,422
And I pray this will become a happy family in Thy sight.
而我也祈祷 它将会是个快乐的家庭

473
00:46:02,626 --> 00:46:05,720
God bless the captain. God bless Liesl and Friedrich.
主保佑舰长，莉莎，费瑞克

474
00:46:05,963 --> 00:46:10,127
God bless Louisa, Brigitta, Marta and little Gretl.
还有露易莎 碧姬塔，犸塔和小葛特儿

475
00:46:10,434 --> 00:46:13,232
And I forgot the other boy. What's his name?
我忘了个男孩 他叫什么名字？

476
00:46:14,972 --> 00:46:16,803
Well, God bless what's-his-name.
总之，主保佑他

477
00:46:17,007 --> 00:46:21,068
God bless the Reverend Mother and Sister Margaretta...
求主赐福院长，犸格丽特修女

478
00:46:21,311 --> 00:46:23,040
...and everybody at the abbey.
和在修道院的每位修女

479
00:46:23,247 --> 00:46:25,807
And now, dear God, about Liesl.
还有主啊，有关莉莎

480
00:46:26,250 --> 00:46:28,138
Help her know that I'm her friend...
让她知道我是她的朋友

481
00:46:28,352 --> 00:46:30,980
...and help her tell me what she's been up to.
让她告诉我，她在干什么

482
00:46:31,588 --> 00:46:32,850
Are you going to tell on me?
你会去告密吗？

483
00:46:33,090 --> 00:46:36,514
Help me to be understanding so I may guide her footsteps.
协助我能了解，让我能指引她

484
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:39,456
In the name of the Father, the Son and the Holy Ghost.
因父，及子，及圣神之名

485
00:46:39,663 --> 00:46:42,655
I was out walking and somebody locked the doors early.
我出去散步，而大门提前关

486
00:46:42,900 --> 00:46:46,563
I didn't want to wake everybody, so when I saw your window open...
我不想吵醒大家 所以当我看见你的窗户是开着时…

487
00:46:48,172 --> 00:46:51,232
You're not going to tell Father, are you?
你不会向父亲告密吧？

488
00:46:57,347 --> 00:46:58,712
How did you climb up?
你是如何攀上来的？

489
00:46:59,116 --> 00:47:02,244
It's how we always got in to play tricks on the governess.
我们常这样进来戏弄家教

490
00:47:02,486 --> 00:47:05,478
Louisa can make it with a whole jar of spiders in her hand.
露易莎能手拿一罐的蜘蛛 单手爬上来呢

491
00:47:06,490 --> 00:47:08,082
Spiders?
蜘蛛？

492
00:47:11,862 --> 00:47:14,490
Were you out walking all by yourself?
你是独自出去散步吗？

493
00:47:21,939 --> 00:47:25,602
If we wash that dress tonight, nobody would notice it tomorrow.
我们今晚将衣服洗好的话 明天就没有人会知道

494
00:47:26,310 --> 00:47:28,107
You could put this on.
你可以穿上这个

495
00:47:29,813 --> 00:47:32,543
Take your dress and put it to soak in the bathtub.
进去里面脱下衣服 泡在浴缸里

496
00:47:32,749 --> 00:47:36,241
Come back here and sit on the bed, and we'll have a talk.
回来坐在床上，我们好好谈

497
00:47:37,588 --> 00:47:40,614
I told you today I didn't need a governess.
我今天告诉你，我不需要家教

498
00:47:40,824 --> 00:47:42,917
Well, maybe I do.
或许我还真的需要

499
00:48:13,423 --> 00:48:15,914
Gretl, are you scared?
葛特儿，你害怕吗？

500
00:48:19,463 --> 00:48:21,761
You're not frightened of a storm, are you?
你不是怕这些雷电吧？

501
00:48:21,965 --> 00:48:24,195
You just stay right here with me.
与我一起就不用怕了

502
00:48:25,435 --> 00:48:29,633
- Where are the others? - They're asleep. They're not scared.
-其他的人呢？ -他们睡着了，他们不怕

503
00:48:34,077 --> 00:48:35,874
Oh, no? Look.
是吗？看

504
00:48:37,447 --> 00:48:39,472
All right, up here on the bed.
好吧，大家都上床来

505
00:48:39,650 --> 00:48:42,380
- Really? - Well, just this once. Come on.
-真的吗？ -只此一次，来吧

506
00:48:43,487 --> 00:48:47,810
- Now we'll wait for the boys. - You won't see them. Boys are brave.
-现在就等男孩们 -他们不会来，男孩们是很勇敢的

507
00:48:53,897 --> 00:48:55,694
You weren't scared, were you?
你们男孩不是也在害怕吧？

508
00:48:56,199 --> 00:48:59,532
Oh, no. We just wanted to be sure that you weren't.
当然不怕 我们只想确定你不害怕

509
00:49:00,537 --> 00:49:03,529
- That's very thoughtful of you. - It wasn't my idea.
-你真周到 -不是我出的主意

510
00:49:03,840 --> 00:49:05,705
It was Kurt's!
是寇特

511
00:49:05,876 --> 00:49:08,606
Kurt! That's the one I left out! God bless Kurt.
