Tea A drink with jam and bread
Tea是配果酱面包的饮品

691
01:02:20,136 --> 01:02:24,061
That will bring us back to
那样我们又回到…

692
01:02:24,307 --> 01:02:31,133
So-do-la-fa-mi-do-re
So do la fa mi do re

693
01:02:31,380 --> 01:02:35,840
So-do-la-fa-ti
So do la fa ti

694
01:02:36,085 --> 01:02:37,746
La-so
La so

695
01:02:41,257 --> 01:02:47,856
Ti-do
Ti do，So do

696
01:02:47,267 --> 01:02:48,757
So-do

697
01:03:02,211 --> 01:03:05,305
The mountains are magnificent, really magnificent.
这些山真是壮观 真是棒透了

698
01:03:05,548 --> 01:03:08,210
- I had them put up just for you. - Oh?
-我特别为你而升起的 -哦？

699
01:03:08,484 --> 01:03:10,679
Even if it's to a height of 10,000 feet...
万尺高山

700
01:03:10,953 --> 01:03:14,445
...Georg always believes in "rising to the occasion."
盖尔总是相信 它的升起是为了特殊场合

701
01:03:14,690 --> 01:03:17,022
Improve the jokes or I'll disinvite you.
你的笑话不改进的话 我就要收回邀请了

702
01:03:17,593 --> 01:03:20,289
You didn't invite me. I invited myself.
你并未邀请我 我是不请自来的

703
01:03:20,463 --> 01:03:23,057
- Naturally. - You needed a chaperone...
-当然 -你需要伴护人

704
01:03:23,232 --> 01:03:26,030
...and I needed a place where the cuisine is superb...
我需要有佳肴…

705
01:03:26,202 --> 01:03:28,932
...the wine cellar unexcelled...
美酒的地方

706
01:03:29,105 --> 01:03:31,733
...and the price perfect.
而价格又公道

707
01:03:32,108 --> 01:03:33,973
Max, you are outrageous.
麦斯，你真的太过分了

708
01:03:34,210 --> 01:03:38,203
Not at all. I'm a very charming sponge.
一点也不，我是很迷人的食客

709
01:03:40,783 --> 01:03:41,977
Listen.
听

710
01:03:44,287 --> 01:03:46,551
That's the Klopmann Monastery Choir.
那是可普曼修道院的唱诗班

711
01:03:49,559 --> 01:03:51,117
They're good.
他们唱得很好

712
01:03:52,228 --> 01:03:53,855
Very good.
非常好

713
01:03:54,630 --> 01:03:57,258
I must explore this area in the next few days.
以后几天里我要探索这地区

714
01:03:57,500 --> 01:04:00,992
Somewhere, a hungry singing group is waiting for Max Detweiler...
在某处，有个渴望被发掘的 合唱团在等我发掘

715
01:04:01,237 --> 01:04:05,526
...to pluck it out and make it famous at the Salzburg Folk Festival.
并在萨尔斯堡的音乐节时 一举成名

716
01:04:05,741 --> 01:04:09,074
- They get fame, you get money. - It's unfair, I admit it.
-他们有名而你就有利 -那不公平，我得承认

717
01:04:09,278 --> 01:04:13,635
But someday that'll be changed. I shall get the fame too.
但有天一切都会改变 我也会成名的

718
01:04:20,723 --> 01:04:22,884
Good heavens, what's this?
天啊，这是怎么回事？

719
01:04:24,293 --> 01:04:26,591
It's nothing. Just some local urchins.
没什么，只是本地的顽童

720
01:04:41,844 --> 01:04:45,769
This really is exciting for me, Georg. Being here with you.
在这里和你在一起 真的让我很兴奋

721
01:04:46,582 --> 01:04:49,142
Trees, lakes, you've seen them before.
树林，湖泽 这些你都已经看过了

722
01:04:49,418 --> 01:04:52,046
That is not what I mean, and you know it.
我不是这个意思 你是知道的

723
01:04:52,288 --> 01:04:56,247
- You mean me? I'm exciting? - Is that so impossible?
-你是指我吗？我令你兴奋？ -不可能吗？

724
01:04:56,492 --> 01:04:59,552
No, just highly improbable.
不是，只是不会发生

725
01:04:59,795 --> 01:05:03,925
- There you go, running yourself down. - Well, I'm a dangerous driver.
-又来了，又看低自己了 -我是危险的驾驶人

726
01:05:07,703 --> 01:05:11,434
You're much less of a riddle when I see you here, Georg.
在这里，我好像比较 容易了解你，盖尔

727
01:05:11,641 --> 01:05:14,474
- In my natural habitat? - Yes, exactly.
-在我生长的地方？ -是的，正是

728
01:05:14,710 --> 01:05:16,974
Are you saying that I'm more at home...
你是说在这

729
01:05:17,146 --> 01:05:21,139
...among the birds and the flowers and the wind that moves...
鸟语花香的地方

730
01:05:21,384 --> 01:05:23,579
...through the trees like a restless sea?
我感觉较舒适？

731
01:05:23,819 --> 01:05:25,377
How poetic.
多有诗意啊

732
01:05:25,621 --> 01:05:27,486
Yes, it was rather, wasn't it?
是的，我是的，不是吗？

733
01:05:28,624 --> 01:05:33,721
More at home here than in Vienna in all your glittering salons...
我觉得在此比在维也纳安逸 在你们那奢华的沙龙里

734
01:05:33,963 --> 01:05:38,320
...gossiping gaily with bores I detest, soaking myself in champagne...
和那些无聊汉附庸风雅喝香槟

735
01:05:38,601 --> 01:05:42,389
...stumbling about to waltzes by Strausses I can't even remember?
被那不知名的华尔兹所牵绊

736
01:05:42,571 --> 01:05:44,801
- Is that what you're saying? - Yes.
-你就是想告诉我这些吗？ -是的

737
01:05:44,974 --> 01:05:47,306
Now whatever gave you that idea?
你为何会有那概念？

738
01:05:50,680 --> 01:05:54,537
Oh, I do like it here, Georg. It's so lovely and peaceful.
我真的喜欢这儿，盖尔 如此可爱和宁静

739
01:05:54,884 --> 01:05:56,840
How can you leave it so often?
你怎舍得经常离开此地？

740
01:05:57,119 --> 01:05:59,917
Oh, pretending to be madly active, I suppose.
我想是假装自己还是很活跃

741
01:06:00,189 --> 01:06:03,386
Activity suggests a life filled with purpose.
活跃使生命看似充满了目的

742
01:06:04,193 --> 01:06:06,423
Could it be running away from memories?
可能是在逃避回忆

743
01:06:09,665 --> 01:06:13,556
Or perhaps just searching for a reason to stay.
也许是在寻求留下的理由

744
01:06:14,236 --> 01:06:17,728
I hope that's why you've been coming to Vienna so often.
我希望那是你 常去维也纳的理由

745
01:06:18,407 --> 01:06:22,730
- Were there other distractions? - I'd hardly call you a distraction.
-还是那儿有让你着魔的事物？ -我不能说是你令我着魔的

746
01:06:23,012 --> 01:06:25,674
Well, what would you call me, Georg?
那你如何形容我，盖尔？

747
01:06:27,917 --> 01:06:29,214
Lovely...
漂亮…

748
01:06:30,152 --> 01:06:32,780
...charming, witty, graceful, the perfect hostess...
美丽，聪明有风度 很完美的女主人

749
01:06:33,055 --> 01:06:35,888
...and, you're going to hate me for this...
你会恨我这样说的：

750
01:06:36,292 --> 01:06:38,385
...in a way, my savior.
有点像是我的救世主

751
01:06:38,661 --> 01:06:40,458
Oh, how unromantic.
真不浪漫呀

752
01:06:40,696 --> 01:06:43,085
I'd be an ungrateful wretch if I didn't say...
如果我不告诉你 那我就是不知感恩的小人了

753
01:06:43,265 --> 01:06:46,530
...that you brought some meaning back into my life.
是你使我重新体会生命的意义

754
01:06:48,371 --> 01:06:51,101
I am amusing, I suppose.
我想我是受宠若惊

755
01:06:51,307 --> 01:06:56,097
I have the finest couturier in Vienna and a glittering circle of friends.
我拥有维也纳最好的地方 最上流的社交圈子的朋友

756
01:06:56,312 --> 01:06:59,440
- I do give some rather gay parties. - Oh, yes.
-和举办最豪华的派对 -是的

757
01:06:59,715 --> 01:07:01,546
But take all that away...
除去那些…

758
01:07:01,751 --> 01:07:06,108
...and you have just wealthy, unattached little me...
我只是一个富有 和飘浮不定的人

759
01:07:06,822 --> 01:07:09,245
...searching, just like you.
在寻寻觅觅，就像你一样

760
01:07:14,330 --> 01:07:16,059
More strudel, Herr Detweiler?
多来点馅饼吗？

761
01:07:16,298 --> 01:07:17,822
- How many have I had? - Two.
-我吃了多少？ -两个了

762
01:07:18,100 --> 01:07:19,988
Make it an uneven three.
那么它就成为第三个吧

763
01:07:23,305 --> 01:07:26,331
Still eating, Max? Must be unhappy.
还在吃，麦斯？ 一定是不太快乐

764
01:07:26,575 --> 01:07:30,500
That mixed quartet I've been trying to steal away from Sol Hurok...
数月来我一直想从何洛克那边 弄来那队四重奏

765
01:07:30,780 --> 01:07:33,442
- What happened? ...Sascha Petrie stole them first.
-发生何事？ -沙夏皮特抢先了

766
01:07:33,649 --> 01:07:34,946
I hate thieves.
我最恨贼了

767
01:07:35,217 --> 01:07:38,482
Max, you really must try and learn to love yourself.
麦斯，你要学习自爱

768
01:07:38,754 --> 01:07:41,086
I had to call Paris, Rome and Stockholm.
为此事我得打长途电话到巴黎 罗马及斯德哥尔摩

769
01:07:41,323 --> 01:07:44,918
- On Georg's telephone, of course. - How else could I afford it?
-当然是用盖尔的电话了 -要不然我怎么负担得起？

770
01:07:45,361 --> 01:07:50,492
I like rich people, the way they live and how I live when I'm with them.
我喜欢有钱人，我喜欢他们的 生活方式，尤其和他们一起生活时

771
01:07:50,800 --> 01:07:52,791
I wonder where the children are.
我在想孩子们上哪儿去了

772
01:07:53,235 --> 01:07:55,760
They must have heard I was coming and hid.
他们一定是听见我来 躲起来了

773
01:07:56,005 --> 01:07:58,496
I was hoping they'd be here to welcome you.
我是希望他们会在家欢迎你的

774
01:07:58,774 --> 01:08:03,268
Max, do step out of character for a moment and try and be charming.
麦斯，试着放开朗一些，好吗？

775
01:08:12,321 --> 01:08:13,686
Well?
怎样？

776
01:08:14,623 --> 01:08:15,817
Well what?
什么怎样？

777
01:08:16,025 --> 01:08:18,949
Have you made up his mind? Do I hear wedding bells?
你让盖尔决定了没？ 我是否会听见婚礼钟声？

778
01:08:19,195 --> 01:08:21,186
- Pealing madly. - Marvelous.
-很有希望 -太棒了

779
01:08:21,464 --> 01:08:24,160
- Not necessarily for me. - What kind of talk's that?
-但不一定跟我有关 -那是什么意思？

780
01:08:24,366 --> 01:08:25,993
None-of-your-business talk.
那跟你无关

781
01:08:26,268 --> 01:08:28,759
I'm terribly fond of him, so don't toy with us.
我很喜欢盖尔 我不准你把我们当玩具

782
01:08:29,004 --> 01:08:32,565
But I'm a child. I like toys. So tell me everything.
但我是个孩子，我喜欢玩具 所以告诉我一切吧

783
01:08:32,842 --> 01:08:37,973
Come on. Tell me every teensy-weensy, intimate, disgusting detail.
快点，告诉麦斯一切的细节

784
01:08:39,415 --> 01:08:43,545
Well, let's just say I have a feeling I may be here on approval.
我有感觉，我来这里的目的 是要得到认可

785
01:08:43,819 --> 01:08:46,845
- I approve of that. How can you miss? - Far too easily.
-我同意了，你怎会错过？ -很容易的

786
01:08:47,089 --> 01:08:50,320
If I know you, darling, and I do, you will find a way.
如我了解你的话 我知道你会找到方法的

787
01:08:50,559 --> 01:08:53,084
- He's no ordinary man. - No, he's rich.
-他不是普通人 -他很富有

788
01:08:53,362 --> 01:08:55,592
His wife's death gave him a great heartache.
他老婆的死 给他带来可怕的心痛

789
01:08:55,831 --> 01:08:58,925
And your husband's death gave you a great fortune.
当你先生死时 他留给你一笔可观的遗产

790
01:08:59,168 --> 01:09:01,090
Oh, Max, you really are a beast.
麦斯，你真是怪物

791
01:09:01,337 --> 01:09:05,364
You and Georg are like family. That's why I want to see you married.
你和盖尔对我来讲，就像是一家人 所以我想看到你们两人结婚

792
01:09:05,574 --> 01:09:09,169
We must keep all that lovely money in the family.
我们必须保留那笔钱 在同一家庭中

793
01:09:25,427 --> 01:09:28,385
- What are you doing there? - Oh, Captain von Trapp.
-你在干什么？ -范舰长

794
01:09:28,631 --> 01:09:30,690
I was just looking for...
我正在找…

795
01:09:31,567 --> 01:09:34,400
I didn't see, I mean, I didn't know you were...
我没看到，我不知道你…

796
01:09:34,970 --> 01:09:36,699
Heil Hitler!
希特勒万岁

797
01:09:37,406 --> 01:09:38,896
Who are you?
你是谁？

798
01:09:39,141 --> 01:09:41,405
I have a telegram for Herr Detweiler.
我送电报给德维勒先生

799
01:09:41,610 --> 01:09:44,408
- I am Herr Detweiler. - Yes, sir.
-我就是 -是的，先生

800
01:09:49,351 --> 01:09:52,115
You've delivered your telegram. Now get out.
好，电报你送到了，滚吧

801
01:09:58,861 --> 01:10:02,217
- Georg, he's just a boy. - Yes, and I'm just an Austrian.
-盖尔，他只是个小男孩 -是，而我只是个奥地利人

802
01:10:02,431 --> 01:10:05,264
Things will happen. Make sure they don't happen to you.
要发生的迟早会发生 只要确定不会发生在你身上

803
01:10:05,434 --> 01:10:08,232
Max! Don't you ever say that again.
麦斯，你别再这样说

804
01:10:08,470 --> 01:10:10,665
I have no political convictions.
你知道我没有政治主张

805
01:10:10,940 --> 01:10:13,795
- Can I help it if other people do? - You can help it.
-人人都如此时我可以怎样？ -有东西可以做的

806
01:10:14,944 --> 01:10:17,139
You must help it.
一定有

807
01:10:27,456 --> 01:10:29,014
Hello?
哈

808
01:10:31,627 --> 01:10:34,460
You're far away. Where are you?
你如此遥远，你在哪儿？

809
01:10:34,763 --> 01:10:38,620
In a world that's disappearing, I'm afraid.
在一个遥不可及的世界里

810
01:10:39,468 --> 01:10:42,995
Is there any way I could bring you back to the world I'm in?
我有办法带你回到现实世界吗？

811
01:11:08,964 --> 01:11:11,489
- Father! Father! - There's your father!
-爸爸，是爸爸！ -是你们爸爸！

812
01:11:12,234 --> 01:11:14,930
Oh, captain, you're home!
哦，舰长，你回来了

813
01:11:23,312 --> 01:11:25,974
Come out of that water at once!
立刻从水里上来

814
01:11:35,024 --> 01:11:37,219
Oh, you must be Baroness Schraeder.
你一定是史蕾特男爵夫人

815
01:11:42,531 --> 01:11:45,557
I'm soaked to the skin!
我湿透了！

816
01:11:57,546 --> 01:11:58,911
Straight line!
排好

817
01:12:13,595 --> 01:12:16,018
This is Baroness Schraeder.
这位是史蕾特男爵夫人

818
01:12:18,600 --> 01:12:20,397
And these...
而这些…

819
01:12:20,602 --> 01:12:22,263
...are my children.
是我的孩子们

820
01:12:23,272 --> 01:12:24,796
How do you do?
你们好

821
01:12:25,908 --> 01:12:30,607
Go inside, dry off, clean up, change your clothes and report back here!
进去屋里，抹干身子，清洁好 换衣服后再回来此地

822
01:12:35,617 --> 01:12:37,710
Fraulein, you will stay here, please!
小姐，请你留下来

823
01:12:39,455 --> 01:12:43,016
I think I'd better go see what Max is up to.
我最好去看麦斯在干什么

824
01:12:53,235 --> 01:12:55,032
Now, fraulein...
小姐…

825
01:12:56,939 --> 01:12:58,964
...I want a truthful answer.
我要你据实回答

826
01:12:59,408 --> 01:13:00,841
Yes, captain.
是的，舰长

827
01:13:01,143 --> 01:13:05,239
Is it possible, or could I have just imagined it?
是真有可能，或只是我的想像…

828
01:13:06,749 --> 01:13:11,174
Have my children, by any chance, been climbing trees today?
我的孩子们今天有爬过树？

829
01:13:11,687 --> 01:13:12,847
Yes, captain.
是的，舰长

830
01:13:13,956 --> 01:13:15,253
I see.
这样

831
01:13:15,824 --> 01:13:20,318
And where, may I ask, did they get these...
我能否请教他们哪来的这些

832
01:13:20,596 --> 01:13:22,655
- Play clothes. - Is that what they are?
-游戏服 -你是如此称呼它们的

833
01:13:22,865 --> 01:13:26,289
I made them from the drapes that used to hang in my bedroom.
是我拿我卧房里的 旧窗帘所做的

834
01:13:27,102 --> 01:13:29,195
- Drapes? - They have plenty of wear left.
-窗帘？ -还剩下很多

835
01:13:29,438 --> 01:13:31,326
We've been everywhere in them.
孩子们穿着玩了不少地方

836
01:13:31,607 --> 01:13:36,101
Are you telling me that my children have been roaming about Salzburg...
你是在告诉我 我的孩子穿着旧窗帘的布料…

837
01:13:36,311 --> 01:13:39,644
...dressed up in nothing but some old drapes?
玩遍了萨尔斯堡？

838
01:13:39,848 --> 01:13:41,509
And having a marvelous time!
而且玩得很开心

839
01:13:41,717 --> 01:13:45,016
- They have uniforms. - Forgive me, straitjackets.
-他们有制服 -对不起那是疯子穿的

840
01:13:45,187 --> 01:13:48,042
They can't be children if they worry about clothes...
孩子们不该担心他们会弄脏 他们珍贵的制服

841
01:13:48,223 --> 01:13:49,451
They don't complain.
我没听过埋怨

842
01:13:49,625 --> 01:13:52,321
They don't dare. They love you too much and fear...
他们不敢，他们太爱你 我想…

843
01:13:52,528 --> 01:13:54,086
Don't discuss my children.
我不想讨论我的孩子们

844
01:13:54,263 --> 01:13:56,219
You've got to hear, you're never home...
你必须听某人说的 你从来不在家久留的

845
01:13:56,465 --> 01:13:57,955
I don't want to hear more!
我不想再听你说 有关我孩子们的事

846
01:13:58,167 --> 01:14:00,692
I know you don't, but you've got to!
我知道你不要，但你必须

847
01:14:01,503 --> 01:14:03,664
- Liesl's not a child. - Not one word...
-就拿莉莎来说吧 -你别再说…

848
01:14:03,906 --> 01:14:06,795
Soon she'll be a woman and you won't even know her.
她快要长成一个女人 但你甚至不了解她

849
01:14:07,042 --> 01:14:10,136
Friedrich wants to be a man but you're not here to show...
费瑞克要像你一样成为男人 但没有人给他作榜样

850
01:14:10,379 --> 01:14:11,744
Don't you dare tell me...
你怎胆敢告诉我儿子的事？

851
01:14:11,980 --> 01:14:15,211
Brigitta could tell you about him. She notices everything.
碧姬塔可以告诉你他的事 她洞悉一切

852
01:14:15,484 --> 01:14:18,612
Kurt acts tough to hide the pain when you ignore him...
还有寇特，他假装强悍 当你漠视他时

853
01:14:18,821 --> 01:14:20,345
...the way you do all of them.
他还要表现出坚强的神情

854
01:14:20,622 --> 01:14:23,011
Louisa, I don't know about yet.
还有露易莎，我还不太了解她

855
01:14:23,258 --> 01:14:26,557
The little ones just want love. Please, love them all.
这些小孩只想要被爱 求求你，舰长，爱他们

856
01:14:26,728 --> 01:14:28,355
I don't care to hear more.
我不想再听你说有关孩子的事

857
01:14:28,530 --> 01:14:32,626
- I am not finished yet, captain! - Oh, yes, you are, captain!
-我还没说完 -是的，你说完了，舰长

858
01:14:34,169 --> 01:14:35,329
Fraulein.
小姐

859
01:14:36,609 --> 01:14:40,739
Now, you will pack your things this minute...
你现在立刻收拾行李

860
01:14:40,943 --> 01:14:43,434
...and return to the abbey.
回去修道院

861
01:14:46,048 --> 01:14:47,413
What's that?
那是什么？

862
01:14:49,151 --> 01:14:50,175
It's singing.
是歌声

863
01:14:50,853 --> 01:14:53,651
Yes, I realize it's singing. But who is singing?
我知道是歌声，但是谁在唱歌？

864
01:14:54,590 --> 01:14:56,182
The children.
孩子们

865
01:14:59,061 --> 01:15:00,392
The children?
孩子们？

866
01:15:00,929 --> 01:15:03,693
I taught them something to sing for the baroness.
我教了他们一首歌 欢迎男爵夫人

867
01:15:09,304 --> 01:15:15,368
My heart wants to sing Every song it hears
群山让我心充满音乐

868
01:15:15,611 --> 01:15:18,205
Every song that it hears
要唱出每支歌

869
01:15:18,447 --> 01:15:24,010
My heart wants to beat like the wings Of the birds that rise
我心震荡像鸟儿翅膀

870
01:15:24,186 --> 01:15:27,280
From the lake to the trees
由湖边飞上树

871
01:15:27,456 --> 01:15:29,048
To the trees
飞上树

872
01:15:29,224 --> 01:15:34,116
My heart wants to sigh Like a chime that flies
我心叹息

873
01:15:34,329 --> 01:15:38,959
From a church on a breeze
像钟声飘扬

874
01:15:39,234 --> 01:15:43,193
To laugh like a brook When it trips and falls
笑声像小溪

875
01:15:43,372 --> 01:15:46,364
Over stones on its way
流过石头跌荡抑扬

876
01:15:46,542 --> 01:15:48,066
On its way
跌荡抑扬

877
01:15:48,243 --> 01:15:52,703
To sing through the night
夜晚歌唱

878
01:15:52,915 --> 01:15:58,581
Like a lark who is learning to pray
像云雀祈祷

879
01:15:58,820 --> 01:16:03,314
I go to the hills
当我奔向山里

880
01:16:03,525 --> 01:16:09,782
When my heart is lonely
心情落寞

881
01:16:10,032 --> 01:16:13,763
I know I will hear
我听到…

882
01:16:14,002 --> 01:16:19,793
What I've heard before
昔日歌声

883
01:16:20,609 --> 01:16:24,841
My heart will be blessed
我心就会歌唱

884
01:16:25,113 --> 01:16:32,042
With the sound of music
因为音乐的响起

885
01:16:32,955 --> 01:16:38,154
And I'll sing...
我要再度…

886
01:16:38,360 --> 01:16:46,483
...once more
歌唱

887
01:17:19,668 --> 01:17:21,465
Edelweiss!
火绒草

888
01:17:25,374 --> 01:17:28,537
You never told me how enchanting your children are.
你从来没有告诉我 你的孩子们如此地可爱

889
01:17:37,185 --> 01:17:38,777
Don't go away.
别走开

890
01:17:43,859 --> 01:17:45,258
Fraulein.
小姐

891
01:17:48,630 --> 01:17:49,824
I...
我的…

892
01:17:51,266 --> 01:17:54,064
...behaved badly. I apologize.
表现很失常，我道歉

893
01:17:55,871 --> 01:17:59,398
I'm far too outspoken. It's one of my worst faults.
我说话太过分了 这是我最大的缺点

894
01:17:59,841 --> 01:18:01,331
You were right.
你说的对

895
01:18:03,779 --> 01:18:05,667
I don't know my children.
我不了解我的孩子们

896
01:18:06,982 --> 01:18:11,078
There's still time, captain. They want so much to be close to you.
仍然有时间，舰长 他们很想接近你

897
01:18:11,386 --> 01:18:15,277
And you brought music back into the house.
你将音乐带回到这个家庭里

898
01:18:16,591 --> 01:18:18,081
I'd forgotten.
我都忘记了

899
01:18:20,796 --> 01:18:22,161
Fraulein.
小姐

900
01:18:24,599 --> 01:18:25,896
I want you to stay.
我要你留下来

901
01:18:29,905 --> 01:18:32,669
I ask you to stay.
我请求你留下来

902
01:18:34,509 --> 01:18:38,001
- Lf I could be of any help. - You have already.
-如果我能帮忙的话 -你已经帮了很多忙

903
01:18:38,580 --> 01:18:39,604
More than you know.
比你知道的更多

904
01:18:59,434 --> 01:19:00,799
Marta.
犸塔

905
01:19:01,470 --> 01:19:02,767
Curtain!
开幕

906
01:19:05,407 --> 01:19:08,706
High on a hill was a lonely goatherd
高高的山上 有个寂寞的牧羊人在唱歌

907
01:19:10,278 --> 01:19:13,509
Loud was the voice Of the lonely goatherd
他的歌声真响亮

908
01:19:14,983 --> 01:19:18,316
Folks in a town That was quite remote heard
偏僻小镇的居民 亦听到他的歌声

909
01:19:19,855 --> 01:19:23,120
Lusty and clear From the goatherd's throat heard
他的歌声雄壮而清脆

910
01:19:34,636 --> 01:19:37,491
Marta. Marta!
犸塔！犸塔！

911
01:19:39,875 --> 01:19:41,866
Gretl, the prince!
葛特儿，王子

912
01:19:43,645 --> 01:19:47,069
A prince on the bridge Of a castle moat heard
城堡的桥上有个王子听到了

913
01:19:48,450 --> 01:19:50,873
Men on a road With a load to tote heard
背着行囊上路的人们也听到了

914
01:19:53,388 --> 01:19:56,687
Men in the midst Of a table d'hote heard
用膳中的人们也听到了

915
01:19:58,026 --> 01:20:01,257
Men drinking beer With the foam afloat heard
喝啤酒的人们也听到了

916
01:20:12,340 --> 01:20:15,468
One little girl In a pale pink coat heard
穿淡粉红色外衣的女孩也听见了

917
01:20:17,112 --> 01:20:20,468
She yodeled back To the lonely goatherd
她唱歌回应那寂寞的牧羊人

918
01:20:21,583 --> 01:20:25,041
Soon her mama With a gleaming gloat heard
她妈妈也欣喜的唱着

919
01:20:26,555 --> 01:20:29,854
What a duet for a girl and goatherd
一个女孩和牧羊人 唱出多好的二重唱呀

920
01:21:16,438 --> 01:21:19,669
One little girl In a pale pink coat heard
穿淡粉红色外衣的女孩也听见了

921
01:21:21,176 --> 01:21:24,475
She yodeled back To the lonely goatherd
她唱歌回应那寂寞的牧羊人

922
01:21:25,814 --> 01:21:29,272
Soon her mama With a gleaming gloat heard
她妈妈也欣喜的唱着

923
01:21:30,685 --> 01:21:33,848
What a duet for a girl and goatherd
一个女孩和牧羊人 唱出多好的二重唱呀

924
01:21:35,557 --> 01:21:37,184
Happy are they
他们多快乐啊

925
01:21:40,195 --> 01:21:43,460
Soon the duet will become a trio
二重唱将要成为三重唱

926
01:22:07,923 --> 01:22:09,481
- Bravo! - Bravo!
-好极了！ -好极了！

927
01:22:09,691 --> 01:22:11,181
Very good!
好极了！

928
01:22:12,994 --> 01:22:14,916
Wonderful!
真精彩！

929
01:22:15,497 --> 01:22:18,660
- Can we keep the puppets, Uncle Max? - Yes, can we?
-麦斯伯伯，可以保留木偶吗？ -可以吗？

930
01:22:18,867 --> 01:22:20,926
Of course you may, my darlings.
你当然可以，亲爱的

931
01:22:21,136 --> 01:22:25,334
Why else did I tell Professor Kohner to send the bill to your father?
不然，我怎能告诉可伦教授 将帐单寄给你父亲

932
01:22:29,077 --> 01:22:30,772
Well done, fraulein.
做得很好，小姐

933
01:22:33,281 --> 01:22:35,169
I really am very much impressed.
我真的很感动

934
01:22:35,450 --> 01:22:37,441
They're your children, captain.
他们是你的孩子

935
01:22:44,626 --> 01:22:46,958
My dear, is there anything you can't do?
你还有什么做不到的事吗？

936
01:22:47,195 --> 01:22:49,527
Well, I'm not sure I'll make a good nun.
我不知自己能否成为好修女

937
01:22:49,731 --> 01:22:52,859
If you have any problems, I'd be happy to help you.
如果有任何问题 我很乐意帮你的

938
01:22:56,004 --> 01:22:57,403
Attention, everyone!
各位请注意

939
01:22:57,572 --> 01:23:01,030
I have an announcement to make. Surprise! Surprise!
我有惊人的事情要宣布 惊喜！惊喜！

940
01:23:01,309 --> 01:23:03,641
Today, after a long and desperate search...
经过一番苦心的寻求

941
01:23:03,878 --> 01:23:08,872
...I have found a most exciting entry for the Salzburg Folk Festival.
我终于找到参加 萨尔斯堡音乐节的合唱团了

942
01:23:09,117 --> 01:23:10,914
Congratulations, Max.
恭喜你，麦斯

943
01:23:11,186 --> 01:23:14,144
And who will you be exploiting this time?
这次是谁要给你利用呢？

944
01:23:15,890 --> 01:23:19,155
- The Saint Ignatius Choir? - Guess again.
-圣伊格森合唱团？ -再猜

945
01:23:19,861 --> 01:23:23,752
Well, let me see now. The Klopmann Choir?
我想，克兰曼歌团？

946
01:23:24,032 --> 01:23:26,364
- No, no, no, no. - No, no?
-不对，不对 -不对？

947
01:23:26,634 --> 01:23:27,828
Tell us.
告诉我们

948
01:23:28,036 --> 01:23:31,494
A singing group all in one family. You'll never guess, Georg.
一个由家庭组成的合唱团 你永远都不会估中的

949
01:23:31,740 --> 01:23:34,629
What a charming idea!
多么好的主意

950
01:23:34,876 --> 01:23:36,673
Whose family?
谁的家庭？

951
01:23:37,545 --> 01:23:39,172
Yours.
你的啊

952
01:23:39,381 --> 01:23:41,679
They'll be the talk of the festival.
他们将会是一大轰动

953
01:23:44,552 --> 01:23:47,544
- Well, now, what's so funny? - You are, Max.
-有何好笑的？ -你很好笑，麦斯

954
01:23:47,789 --> 01:23:50,917
You're expensive, but very funny.
很昂贵，但很好笑

955
01:23:51,693 --> 01:23:54,025
- They'll be a sensation! - No, Max.
-他们一定会相当轰动的 -不，麦斯

956
01:23:54,262 --> 01:23:56,423
It's a wonderful idea. Fresh, original.
是极好的主意 新面孔又自然

957
01:23:56,664 --> 01:24:01,454
Max! My children do not sing in public.
麦斯，我的孩子们不公开演唱

958
01:24:02,170 --> 01:24:04,092
You can't blame me for trying.
不能怪我没尝试过

959
01:24:04,305 --> 01:24:07,297
Children, who shall we hear from next?
孩子们，下一个该谁唱？

960
01:24:10,111 --> 01:24:11,271
Who?
谁唱？

961
01:24:17,419 --> 01:24:18,681
Yes.
对

962
01:24:21,556 --> 01:24:23,444
The vote is unanimous.
全体一致通过

963
01:24:24,292 --> 01:24:25,884
You, captain.
由你演唱，舰长

964
01:24:26,127 --> 01:24:27,321
Me?
我？

965
01:24:28,196 --> 01:24:30,460
- I don't understand. - Please.
-我不懂 -拜托

966
01:24:36,704 --> 01:24:38,797
No, no, no, no.
不…

967
01:24:39,074 --> 01:24:41,099
I'm told that you were quite good.
我听说，很久以前 你唱的非常好

968
01:24:41,309 --> 01:24:44,665
- That was a very, very long time ago. - I remember, Father.
-那是非常非常久之前 -我还记得，父亲

969
01:24:44,846 --> 01:24:47,770
- Play us something we know. - Oh, please, Father.
-请为我们唱一首 -求求你，父亲

970
01:24:50,652 --> 01:24:51,744
Well...
这个…

971
01:25:02,030 --> 01:25:04,191
- Why didn't you tell me? - What?
-你为何不告诉我？ -什么？

972
01:25:04,466 --> 01:25:06,798
To bring along my harmonica.
带我的口琴来

973
