Edelweiss
火绒草

998
01:26:59,681 --> 01:27:09,613
Bless my homeland forever
永远守护我的家乡

999
01:27:18,833 --> 01:27:22,530
Anytime you say the word, Georg, you can be part of my new act:
只要你随时开口 就可以加入我的新节目

1000
01:27:22,770 --> 01:27:25,261
The von Trapp Family Singers.
范崔普家庭合唱团

1001
01:27:26,341 --> 01:27:28,832
I have a wonderful idea, Georg.
我有个好主意

1002
01:27:29,110 --> 01:27:31,533
Let's really fill this house with music.
让此屋中充满音乐

1003
01:27:31,813 --> 01:27:34,771
You must give a grand and glorious party for me.
你要为我开个盛大的舞会

1004
01:27:35,016 --> 01:27:37,712
- A party? - Yes, Father, please!
-派对？ -是的，好吧，爸爸！

1005
01:27:37,885 --> 01:27:40,308
It's high time I met all your friends...
我想我该认识 你在萨尔斯堡的朋友了

1006
01:27:40,555 --> 01:27:43,115
...and they met me. Don't you agree?
你不同意吗？

1007
01:27:43,358 --> 01:27:45,622
- I see what you mean. - Oh, please!
-我明白你的意思 -好吧，爸爸！

1008
01:27:45,860 --> 01:27:49,023
Children, it's bedtime. Come now, say good night.
孩子们，该上床了 道晚安

1009
01:27:49,964 --> 01:27:51,226
Good night, Father.
晚安，父亲

1010
01:27:51,499 --> 01:27:54,297
- Good night. - Good night, Baroness Schraeder.
-晚安 -晚安，男爵夫人

1011
01:27:54,535 --> 01:27:56,127
Good night, Father.
晚安，父亲

1012
01:27:59,073 --> 01:28:00,938
Good night, Uncle Max.
晚安，麦斯伯伯

1013
01:28:02,844 --> 01:28:06,007
It'll be my first party, Father!
那将会是我的第一次舞会，父亲

1014
01:28:38,546 --> 01:28:41,174
- Captain. - Herr Zeller. Baroness Schraeder.
-舰长 -你好，吉勒先生，男爵夫人

1015
01:28:41,382 --> 01:28:44,510
- Good evening, Herr Zeller. - Baroness.
-你好，吉勒先生 -男爵夫人

1016
01:28:45,787 --> 01:28:48,278
How do you do? Good evening.
你好

1017
01:29:08,910 --> 01:29:12,300
Did you notice the obvious display of the Austrian flag?
我想你注意到大厅上当眼处 挂着奥地利国旗

1018
01:29:19,420 --> 01:29:21,217
The women look so beautiful.
女人们看来好漂亮

1019
01:29:21,456 --> 01:29:22,753
I think they look ugly.
我觉得她们好丑

1020
01:29:23,091 --> 01:29:24,888
You're just scared of them.
你这样说是因为你怕她们

1021
01:29:25,093 --> 01:29:27,391
Silly, only grown-up men fear women.
傻瓜！只有成人才会怕女人

1022
01:29:27,962 --> 01:29:31,557
- I think the men look beautiful. - How would you know?
-我认为男人看来好美 -你怎么会知道？

1023
01:29:48,783 --> 01:29:50,808
Liesl, who are you dancing with?
莉莎，你在跟谁跳舞？

1024
01:29:51,052 --> 01:29:52,679
Nobody.
没有人

1025
01:29:53,488 --> 01:29:55,410
Oh, yes, you are.
哦，的确没有

1026
01:29:57,859 --> 01:29:59,349
May I have this dance?
我有这份荣幸吗？

1027
01:29:59,594 --> 01:30:02,085
I'd be delighted, young man.
我很乐意的，年轻人

1028
01:30:08,803 --> 01:30:11,499
Why didn't you tell me you could dance?
你们为何不告诉我 你们会跳舞？

1029
01:30:11,773 --> 01:30:16,665
We feared you'd make us all dance. The von Trapp Family Dancers.
我们怕你会叫我们一起跳舞 范崔普家庭舞蹈团

1030
01:30:21,115 --> 01:30:22,810
What are they playing?
他们在演奏什么？

1031
01:30:23,017 --> 01:30:25,645
It's the Laendler. An Austrian folk dance.
那是奥地利的一种民俗舞曲

1032
01:30:25,820 --> 01:30:29,017
- Show me. - I haven't danced since I was little.
-教我们 -我很久没跳过了

1033
01:30:29,223 --> 01:30:31,179
You remember. Please?
你记得的，求求你

1034
01:30:31,459 --> 01:30:33,381
- Well... - Please.
-这个… -拜托嘛

1035
01:30:33,661 --> 01:30:35,856
All right. Come on over here.
好吧，过来

1036
01:30:36,364 --> 01:30:39,197
Now you bow and I curtsy.
现在你鞠躬，我答礼

1037
01:30:40,134 --> 01:30:43,092
- Like this? - Fine. Now we go for a little walk.
-像这样 -很好，现在我们走几步！

1038
01:30:43,337 --> 01:30:45,999
One, two, three. One, two, three.
1，2，3，1，2，3

1039
01:30:46,240 --> 01:30:50,870
One, two, three, step together. Now, step hop, step hop.
1，2，3，一起踏步 踏步跳…

1040
01:30:51,145 --> 01:30:53,807
Now turn under. Not quite.
转圈

1041
01:30:54,015 --> 01:30:57,974
This way. Hop step, hop. And under.
这边，踏步跳，转圈

1042
01:30:58,653 --> 01:31:00,348
Kurt, we'll have to practice.
我们要好好练习呢

1043
01:31:00,555 --> 01:31:02,045
Do allow me, will you?
让我来跳好吗？

1044
01:32:30,344 --> 01:32:32,232
I don't remember anymore.
我不记得了

1045
01:32:34,415 --> 01:32:36,610
- Your face is all red. - Is it?
-你的脸好红 -是吗？

1046
01:32:37,919 --> 01:32:40,012
I don't suppose I'm used to dancing.
我想我不习惯跳舞吧

1047
01:32:42,757 --> 01:32:44,748
Why, that was beautifully done.
那真是跳得太棒了

1048
01:32:44,959 --> 01:32:46,915
What a lovely couple you make.
你们是迷人的一对

1049
01:32:47,128 --> 01:32:49,323
It's time the children said good night.
我想孩子们该上床了

1050
01:32:49,497 --> 01:32:50,896
We'll be in the hall.
我们马上去前厅

1051
01:32:51,065 --> 01:32:54,023
- We have something special prepared. - Right!
-我们有特别节目 -是的

1052
01:32:54,201 --> 01:32:55,429
Yes, come on!
是的，快点

1053
01:33:02,276 --> 01:33:04,608
All that needless worrying, Georg.
盖尔，你的担心看来是多余的

1054
01:33:04,845 --> 01:33:07,871
You thought you wouldn't find a friend at the party.
你还以为自己在 舞会上找不到朋友

1055
01:33:10,818 --> 01:33:14,447
- A bit chilly out tonight, isn't it? - Oh, I don't know.
-今晚外面有点凉，是不是？ -不，我不知道

1056
01:33:14,622 --> 01:33:16,613
It seemed rather warm to me.
我觉得颇暖和呢！

1057
01:33:20,895 --> 01:33:22,021
Ladies and gentlemen.
先生女士们！

1058
01:33:22,797 --> 01:33:26,858
The children of Captain von Trapp wish to say good night to you.
范崔普舰长的孩子 希望向各位道晚安！

1059
01:33:41,015 --> 01:33:44,872
There's a sad sort of clanging From the clock in the hall
忧愁的钟声来自大厅

1060
01:33:45,086 --> 01:33:48,852
And the bells in the steeple too
塔尖的钟声也响起了

1061
01:33:49,090 --> 01:33:53,083
And up in the nursery An absurd little bird
在孩子们卧室里 一只滑稽的小鸟

1062
01:33:53,361 --> 01:33:55,784
Is popping up to say "coo-coo"
伸出头来道咕咕

1063
01:33:56,030 --> 01:33:57,691
Coo-coo
咕咕

1064
01:33:57,932 --> 01:33:59,160
Coo-coo
咕咕

1065
01:33:59,400 --> 01:34:01,561
Regretfully they tell us
很抱歉他告诉我们

1066
01:34:01,802 --> 01:34:03,167
But firmly they compel us
要我们向大家

1067
01:34:03,404 --> 01:34:06,532
To say goodbye
道晚安

1068
01:34:06,707 --> 01:34:11,997
To you
向大家

1069
01:34:15,216 --> 01:34:19,038
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, good night
别了，再见，珍重晚安

1070
01:34:19,220 --> 01:34:23,111
I hate to go And leave this pretty sight
我不愿离开如斯美景

1071
01:34:30,398 --> 01:34:33,731
So long, farewell, Auf Wiedersehen, adieu
别了，再见，珍重再见

1072
01:34:34,402 --> 01:34:37,929
Adieu, adieu To you and you and you
我向你和你和你说声再见

1073
01:34:45,346 --> 01:34:49,077
So long, farewell Au revoir, auf Wiedersehen
别了，再见，珍重再见

1074
01:34:49,383 --> 01:34:53,342
I'd like to stay And taste my first champagne
我能否留下喝第一口香槟？

1075
01:34:53,587 --> 01:34:55,976
- Yes? - No.
-可以吗？ -不行

1076
01:35:00,361 --> 01:35:03,956
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, goodbye
别了，再见，珍重再见

1077
01:35:04,365 --> 01:35:08,290
I leave and heave a sigh And say goodbye
我轻叹着离开并说再见

1078
01:35:08,502 --> 01:35:12,495
Goodbye
再见

1079
01:35:15,576 --> 01:35:18,739
I'm glad to go
我真高兴可以离去

1080
01:35:18,913 --> 01:35:21,746
I cannot tell a lie
我不能说谎

1081
01:35:22,116 --> 01:35:25,108
I flit, I float
我展翅，我飘浮

1082
01:35:25,386 --> 01:35:28,810
I fleetly flee, I fly
我地消失，我在飞翔

1083
01:35:38,833 --> 01:35:44,590
The sun has gone to bed
太阳已就

1084
01:35:44,839 --> 01:35:48,536
And so must I
我也一样

1085
01:35:48,776 --> 01:35:51,165
So long
别了

1086
01:35:51,445 --> 01:35:53,970
Farewell
再见

1087
01:35:54,181 --> 01:35:59,608
Auf Wiedersehen, goodbye
珍重晚安

1088
01:35:59,854 --> 01:36:05,144
Goodbye
晚安

1089
01:36:05,926 --> 01:36:11,489
Goodbye
晚安

1090
01:36:11,699 --> 01:36:18,559
Goodbye
晚安

1091
01:36:18,806 --> 01:36:27,236
Goodbye
晚安

1092
01:36:32,353 --> 01:36:35,083
Extraordinary! What they'd do at the festival.
他们真是不同凡响 想想在音乐节的成绩

1093
01:36:35,356 --> 01:36:37,779
Young lady, I must have a word with you.
年轻女士，我必须跟你谈谈

1094
01:36:38,793 --> 01:36:42,889
Georg, you won't let this girl get away. She must join the party.
盖尔，你不能让她离去的 她必须参加派对

1095
01:36:43,063 --> 01:36:45,554
- No, really l... - Stop. Stop it now.
-不，我真的… -别说了

1096
01:36:45,766 --> 01:36:48,724
- Georg, please. - You can if you want to, fraulein.
-盖尔，拜托 -如你愿意的话，可以留下来

1097
01:36:48,936 --> 01:36:51,427
I insist. You will be my dinner partner.
我坚持，你会是我今晚的女伴

1098
01:36:51,639 --> 01:36:53,561
This is business. Franz...
这是生意 福兰斯…

1099
01:36:53,808 --> 01:36:57,005
...set another place next to mine for Fraulein Maria.
在我的座位旁 替犸莉亚小姐加一个位子

1100
01:36:59,146 --> 01:37:01,910
- Whatever you say. - It appears to be all arranged.
-悉听尊便 -似乎已安排好了

1101
01:37:02,650 --> 01:37:04,538
- It does. - I'm not suitably dressed.
-是的 -我的打扮不适合

1102
01:37:05,619 --> 01:37:07,143
You can change. We'll wait.
你可以换衣服，我们等你

1103
01:37:10,758 --> 01:37:13,613
Captain, you must be very proud of your youngsters.
舰长，你一定 很以你的儿女为荣

1104
01:37:13,794 --> 01:37:14,818
I am, thank you.
是的，谢谢你

1105
01:37:15,029 --> 01:37:19,557
Is there a more beautiful expression of what is good in our country...
还有什么比孩子们纯真的歌声

1106
01:37:19,800 --> 01:37:23,258
...than the innocent voices of our children?
更能表现我国的优点？

1107
01:37:23,637 --> 01:37:25,036
Oh, come now, baron.
对了，男爵

1108
01:37:25,272 --> 01:37:29,038
Would you have us believe that Austria holds a monopoly on virtue?
你想要我们相信 只有奥地利有独特高尚的品德？

1109
01:37:29,910 --> 01:37:34,040
Herr Zeller, some of us prefer Austrian voices raised in song...
我们有些人喜欢 悠扬的奥地利歌声

1110
01:37:34,281 --> 01:37:36,647
...to ugly German threats.
多于丑陋的德国威胁

1111
01:37:37,751 --> 01:37:41,312
The ostrich buries his head in the sand...
鸵鸟喜欢埋首于沙中

1112
01:37:41,589 --> 01:37:44,478
...and sometimes in the flag.
有时藏于国旗里

1113
01:37:45,059 --> 01:37:49,257
Perhaps those who would warn you that the Anschluss is coming, and it is...
或许有些人警告过你合并就要 来临了，而事实上是的

1114
01:37:49,496 --> 01:37:53,193
...would get further with you by setting their words to music.
或许会以音乐来跟你打交道呢

1115
01:37:53,434 --> 01:37:58,064
If the Nazis take over Austria, you will be the entire trumpet section.
如果纳粹占据奥地利 你肯定会是整个小号队

1116
01:37:58,372 --> 01:37:59,430
You flatter me.
你太恭维我了

1117
01:38:00,474 --> 01:38:04,331
Oh, how clumsy of me. I meant to accuse you.
我真笨拙 我是要指责你的

1118
01:38:12,119 --> 01:38:14,610
It's very kind of you to offer to help me, baroness.
你愿意来协助我 真的太仁慈了，男爵夫人

1119
01:38:14,822 --> 01:38:16,449
I'm delighted, Maria.
我很乐意

1120
01:38:16,857 --> 01:38:20,623
I really don't think I have anything that would be appropriate.
但我实在没有任何合适的衣服

1121
01:38:21,095 --> 01:38:25,191
Now where is that lovely little thing you were wearing the other evening?
那晚你穿的那件迷人衣服呢？

1122
01:38:25,466 --> 01:38:28,731
When the captain couldn't keep his eyes off you.
使舰长无法将视线从你身上移开

1123
01:38:32,139 --> 01:38:33,970
Couldn't keep his eyes off me?
无法转移他的目光？

1124
01:38:35,242 --> 01:38:37,107
Come, my dear, we are women.
算了吧，亲爱的，我们都是女人

1125
01:38:37,344 --> 01:38:40,677
Let's not pretend we don't know when a man notices us.
别再假装我们不知道 男人在注意我们

1126
01:38:40,915 --> 01:38:44,373
- Here we are. - The captain notices everybody.
-找到了 -舰长他注意到每个人

1127
01:38:44,919 --> 01:38:47,410
There's no need to feel so defensive, Maria.
你无需如此抗拒的，犸莉亚

1128
01:38:47,655 --> 01:38:50,044
You are quite attractive, you know.
你很迷人，你知道吗？

1129
01:38:50,324 --> 01:38:53,987
The captain would hardly be a man if he didn't notice you.
如果舰长不注意你的话 他就不是男人了

1130
01:38:55,529 --> 01:38:57,918
Baroness, I hope you're joking.
男爵夫人，我希望你在开玩笑

1131
01:38:58,399 --> 01:38:59,661
Not at all.
一点也不

1132
01:38:59,900 --> 01:39:01,492
I've never done a thing to...
但我从没做过任何…

1133
01:39:01,735 --> 01:39:03,362
You don't have to, my dear.
你无需如此

1134
01:39:04,004 --> 01:39:08,759
Nothing's more irresistible to a man than a woman who's in love with him.
对男人而言，没什么比 深爱自己的女人更无法抗拒

1135
01:39:10,044 --> 01:39:12,535
- In love with him? - Of course.
-爱他吗？ -是的

1136
01:39:13,447 --> 01:39:16,871
What makes it so nice is he thinks he's in love with you.
最棒的是他也认为自己爱上你了

1137
01:39:19,586 --> 01:39:21,213
But that's not true.
但那不是事实

1138
01:39:21,555 --> 01:39:25,082
Surely you've noticed the way he looks into your eyes.
你当然也注意到 他直视你双眼时的神情吧

1139
01:39:25,359 --> 01:39:30,251
And you know, you blushed in his arms when you were dancing just now.
而刚才当他拥着你跳舞时 你脸红了

1140
01:39:31,532 --> 01:39:33,227
Don't take it to heart.
别太介意

1141
01:39:33,467 --> 01:39:35,765
He'll get over it soon enough, I think.
他很快就会适应的

1142
01:39:36,036 --> 01:39:37,958
Men do, you know.
男人都是如此的

1143
01:39:39,039 --> 01:39:40,063
Then I should go.
那我必须离开了

1144
01:39:41,408 --> 01:39:42,898
I mustn't stay here.
我不能留在此地

1145
01:39:53,387 --> 01:39:56,743
- Is there something I can do to help? - No, nothing.
-我能帮什么忙吗？ -没有

1146
01:39:58,592 --> 01:39:59,786
Yes.
有的

1147
01:40:00,794 --> 01:40:02,819
Don't say a word to the captain.
求你别告诉舰长这件事

1148
01:40:04,465 --> 01:40:07,992
No, I wouldn't dream of it.
不，我不会的

1149
01:40:14,775 --> 01:40:16,402
Goodbye, Maria.
再见，犸莉亚

1150
01:40:17,211 --> 01:40:19,975
I'm sure you'll make a very fine nun.
我相信你会成为很好的修女

1151
01:40:50,010 --> 01:40:52,001
Champagne, darling.
香槟

1152
01:40:52,446 --> 01:40:56,371
I feel like celebrating. Cheers.
我觉得该庆祝一下，干杯

1153
01:41:01,889 --> 01:41:04,778
- You know something. - Perhaps.
-你知道什么吧 -或许吧

1154
01:41:05,025 --> 01:41:09,553
If you're so clever, tell me how to get fraulein to influence Georg.
若你如此聪明 告诉我如何令犸莉亚影响盖尔

1155
01:41:09,830 --> 01:41:12,458
I want those children in the festival.
我要这些孩子参加音乐节

1156
01:41:12,866 --> 01:41:15,198
Elsa, this is important to Austria.
这对奥地利深具意义

1157
01:41:15,369 --> 01:41:17,200
Wouldn't do you any harm either.
对你也不会有妨害的

1158
01:41:17,371 --> 01:41:18,895
I thought of that.
我曾想过

1159
01:41:19,173 --> 01:41:21,664
Well, if it's a matter of influence...
谈到影响

1160
01:41:21,842 --> 01:41:24,766
...maybe the one you have to be talking to is me.
你该找我谈才对

1161
01:42:30,844 --> 01:42:43,507
（中场休息）

1162
01:42:50,797 --> 01:44:40,521
（幕间休息）

1163
01:44:55,151 --> 01:44:57,415
- Two. - Three.
-2 -3

1164
01:44:57,654 --> 01:44:59,144
- Four. - Five.
-4 -5

1165
01:45:00,423 --> 01:45:02,448
- Six. - Seven.
-6 -7

1166
01:45:02,725 --> 01:45:04,283
Eight.

1167
01:45:04,594 --> 01:45:06,391
- Four. - Two.
-4 -2

1168
01:45:07,530 --> 01:45:09,327
- Seven. - Five.
-7 -5

1169
01:45:09,565 --> 01:45:11,795
- Two. - Six.
-2 -6

1170
01:45:16,439 --> 01:45:18,464
Isn't this fun?
真好玩！

1171
01:45:19,809 --> 01:45:22,232
- Four. - I'm number five.
-4 -我是5号

1172
01:45:22,478 --> 01:45:24,639
- Oh, yes. - Eight.
-是的 -8

1173
01:45:24,914 --> 01:45:27,280
- Two. - Four.
-2 -4

1174
01:45:27,684 --> 01:45:28,912
Six.

1175
01:45:31,421 --> 01:45:32,649
Two.

1176
01:45:33,790 --> 01:45:36,759
Baroness Schraeder, do you mind if we stop now? We're tired.
男爵夫人，我们累了 不要玩了

1177
01:45:36,993 --> 01:45:38,949
Whatever you want, dear.
随便你们

1178
01:45:39,229 --> 01:45:41,220
We'll do it again tomorrow.
明天再玩

1179
01:45:51,374 --> 01:45:53,569
The country's so restful, isn't it?
乡间真安静，是不是？

1180
01:45:54,610 --> 01:45:56,202
Have some lemonade.
喝点柠檬水吧

1181
01:45:57,480 --> 01:45:58,879
There must be an easier way.
一定有更容易的办法

1182
01:46:00,283 --> 01:46:03,582
I get a fiendish delight thinking of you as the mother of seven.
想到你做七个孩子的母亲 真令我哭笑不得

1183
01:46:04,520 --> 01:46:06,351
How do you plan to do it?
你计划如何做呢？

1184
01:46:06,622 --> 01:46:08,647
Darling, haven't you ever heard...
你没听过

1185
01:46:08,891 --> 01:46:12,019
...of a delightful little thing called boarding school?
寄宿学校吗？

1186
01:46:13,129 --> 01:46:15,393
Baroness Machiavelli.
你真是诡计多端

1187
01:46:16,733 --> 01:46:18,826
Uncle Max, where's Father?
麦伯伯，爸爸在哪？

1188
01:46:19,001 --> 01:46:20,832
I think he's in the house.
我想他在屋子里

1189
01:46:21,037 --> 01:46:23,597
What's the matter with all you gloomy pussies?
你们为何都闷闷不乐呢？

1190
01:46:23,840 --> 01:46:26,536
- Nothing. - I know. Let's have a rehearsal.
-没什么 -我知道怎么办，我们来做排练

1191
01:46:26,709 --> 01:46:27,733
What for?
为了什么呢？

1192
01:46:27,910 --> 01:46:30,401
Let's make believe we're on-stage at the festival.
假装站在节庆的表演台上

1193
01:46:30,646 --> 01:46:34,503
- I don't feel like singing. - Not without Fraulein Maria.
-我不想唱 -没有犸莉亚我不想唱

1194
01:46:34,751 --> 01:46:37,174
Liesl, get the guitar. Come on, Marta.
莉莎去拿吉他，来吧

1195
01:46:37,353 --> 01:46:40,413
Everybody into the group. Get in your places.
大家站好，各就各位

1196
01:46:40,590 --> 01:46:43,354
Now be cheerful, right? Give us the key, Liesl.
高兴点 丽莎，给我们调子

1197
01:46:45,261 --> 01:46:47,923
Now, impress me.
现在，开始

1198
01:46:51,934 --> 01:46:53,265
Gretl, why don't you sing?
葛特儿，你为何不唱呢？

1199
01:46:53,569 --> 01:46:56,060
I can't. I've got a sore finger.
我手指痛不能唱

1200
01:46:57,073 --> 01:46:58,506
But you sang so beautifully the night of the party.
但是你在舞会中唱得很好

1201
01:47:00,543 --> 01:47:02,636
Come on, all of you. Try something you know.
来，试试看 唱些你们都懂的

1202
01:47:02,879 --> 01:47:04,369
Enjoy it. Be cheerful.
好好享受，快乐些

1203
01:47:04,647 --> 01:47:06,239
All right, Liesl.
好了，莉莎

1204
01:47:08,217 --> 01:47:13,610
The hills are alive
群山因为音乐

1205
01:47:13,856 --> 01:47:21,513
With the sound of music
充满生气

1206
01:47:22,732 --> 01:47:27,760
With songs they have sung
唱了

1207
01:47:28,037 --> 01:47:35,864
For a thousand years
千年的歌

1208
01:47:36,546 --> 01:47:41,939
The hills fill my heart
群山让我的心中

1209
01:47:42,218 --> 01:47:48,680
With the sound of music
充满了音乐

1210
01:47:50,760 --> 01:47:52,887
They wanted to sing for me, bless their hearts.
他们是唱给我听

1211
01:47:53,162 --> 01:47:55,050
That's lovely, lovely. Don't stop.
很好…别停下来

1212
01:47:59,068 --> 01:48:02,959
- Something long and cool, Georg? - No, thank you, darling.
-你喝点饮料吧 -不，谢谢，亲爱的

1213
01:48:03,406 --> 01:48:05,772
- Father? - Yes, Brigitta?
-爸爸 -是的，碧姬塔

1214
01:48:06,275 --> 01:48:08,539
Is it true Fraulein Maria isn't coming back?
犸莉亚不回来吗？

1215
01:48:08,811 --> 01:48:11,905
Yes, I suppose it's true. What have we got here?
是的，我想是不回来了 有什么好喝吗？

1216
01:48:12,248 --> 01:48:16,947
- Pink lemonade. - Laced with lemonade.
-粉红柠檬水 -是柠檬水

1217
01:48:17,687 --> 01:48:19,177
I don't believe it, Father.
父亲，我不敢相信

1218
01:48:20,590 --> 01:48:22,615
- What? - About Fraulein Maria.
-不相信什么？ -关于犸莉亚

1219
01:48:22,992 --> 01:48:24,254
Oh, Fraulein Maria!
哦，犸莉亚

1220
01:48:24,494 --> 01:48:27,986
Didn't I tell you what her note said? I'm sure I did.
我没把她的留言告诉你们吗？ 我肯定我说过了

1221
01:48:28,731 --> 01:48:31,256
She said she missed her life at the abbey.
她说她很怀念修道院的生活

1222
01:48:31,501 --> 01:48:33,662
She had to leave us.
她必须离开我们

1223
01:48:33,836 --> 01:48:35,497
And that's all there is to it.
就这样

1224
01:48:37,240 --> 01:48:39,902
I think I'm brave enough to try some of that.
好，我现在想尝点柠檬水

1225
01:48:40,109 --> 01:48:42,839
- She didn't even say goodbye. - She did in her note.
-她甚至没有告别 -她在留言上有说

1226
01:48:43,112 --> 01:48:44,943
That isn't the same thing.
那是不同的事

1227
01:48:45,214 --> 01:48:46,841
Not too sweet, not too sour.
不甜不酸

1228
01:48:47,617 --> 01:48:49,608
Just too pink.
只是太粉红了

1229
01:48:51,020 --> 01:48:54,148
Father, who is our new governess going to be?
父亲，谁是我们的新家庭老师？

1230
01:49:00,796 --> 01:49:01,820
Well...
这个…

1231
01:49:04,166 --> 01:49:09,456
...you're not going to have a governess anymore.
你们再也没有新家庭老师了

1232
01:49:09,805 --> 01:49:12,433
- We're not? - No.
-我们没有？ -没有

1233
01:49:14,677 --> 01:49:16,804
You're going to have a new mother.
你们将要有个新妈妈

1234
01:49:17,880 --> 01:49:19,939
A new mother?
一个新妈妈？

1235
01:49:20,750 --> 01:49:23,878
We talked about it last night. It's all settled.
我们昨晚谈过了 一切都决定好了

1236
01:49:24,120 --> 01:49:26,816
And we're all going to be very happy.
我们都将会很快乐

1237
01:49:59,822 --> 01:50:02,313
Well, all right, all right. Run off and play.
好了…去玩吧

1238
01:50:34,223 --> 01:50:35,247
Yes, my children?
是的，孩子们

1239
01:50:35,424 --> 01:50:37,813
- My name is Liesl. - Yes, Liesl?
-我叫莉莎 -怎么了，丽莎？

1240
01:50:38,327 --> 01:50:42,252
We, my brothers and sisters, want to see Fraulein Maria.
我们，我的兄弟姐妹们 要见犸莉亚小姐

1241
01:50:43,432 --> 01:50:45,423
Fraulein Maria?
犸莉亚小姐？

1242
01:50:46,135 --> 01:50:48,126
Oh, Maria.
哦，犸莉亚

1243
01:50:50,072 --> 01:50:51,903
Come in, please.
请进来

1244
01:50:55,845 --> 01:50:57,335
Wait here.
在此等一下

1245
01:51:08,257 --> 01:51:11,454
I'm Sister Margaretta. I understand you inquired about Maria.
我是犸格丽特修女 我知道你们想见犸莉亚

1246
01:51:11,627 --> 01:51:14,221
We have to see her. Will you tell her we're here?
我们必须见她 请你告诉她我们在此

1247
01:51:14,463 --> 01:51:17,057
- I'm afraid I can't do that. - But you've got to!
-恐怕我做不到 -你一定要告诉她

1248
01:51:17,299 --> 01:51:19,392
- She's our governess. - We want her back.
-她是我们的家庭教师 -我们要她回来

1249
01:51:19,602 --> 01:51:21,433
She didn't even say goodbye.
她甚至没有道别

1250
01:51:21,771 --> 01:51:23,500
All we want to do is talk to her.
我们想要做的只是和她说话

1251
01:51:24,306 --> 01:51:27,161
I'm very sorry, but Maria is in seclusion.
我很抱歉，孩子们 但是犸莉亚在静修

1252
01:51:27,443 --> 01:51:30,571
- She hasn't been seeing anyone. - She'll see us.
-她不愿见任何人 -她会见我们的

1253
01:51:30,746 --> 01:51:33,271
I want to show her my finger.
我要让她看我的手指

1254
01:51:33,482 --> 01:51:35,313
Some other time, dear.
亲爱的，改天吧

1255
01:51:35,484 --> 01:51:36,974
I'll tell her you were here.
我会告诉她，你们来过

1256
01:51:37,186 --> 01:51:40,280
- It was sweet of you to call. - We have to speak to her!
-很高兴你们来过 -我们要见犸莉亚

1257
01:51:40,923 --> 01:51:44,017
Run along, children. Run along home.
孩子们，回家吧

1258
01:51:44,260 --> 01:51:45,921
I'm sure she'd like to see us.
我肯定她会见我们

1259
01:51:46,162 --> 01:51:48,426
Sister Margaretta, please.
求求你啊

1260
01:51:48,631 --> 01:51:52,397
- Goodbye, children. - Sister Margaretta, may we, please?
-再见，孩子们 -求求你啊

1261
01:51:55,171 --> 01:51:56,900
What was that about, Sister?
那是怎么回事，犸格丽特修女？

1262
01:51:57,139 --> 01:51:59,300
The von Trapp children, Reverend Mother.
院长，范崔普家的孩子

1263
01:51:59,542 --> 01:52:02,033
They want to see Maria.
他们要见犸莉亚

1264
01:52:02,278 --> 01:52:04,610
Has she spoken yet? Has she told you anything?
她说了没？ 她有没有告诉你什么事？

1265
01:52:04,847 --> 01:52:08,840
She doesn't say a word, Reverend Mother, except in prayer.
院长，除了祈祷外 她什么也没说

1266
01:52:09,118 --> 01:52:10,142
Poor child.
可怜的孩子

1267
01:52:10,319 --> 01:52:13,277
It's strange. She seems happy to be back here...
很奇怪，她似乎很高兴能回来

1268
01:52:13,522 --> 01:52:16,787
...and yet she's unhappy too.
但同时又很不快乐

1269
01:52:18,027 --> 01:52:21,155
Perhaps I have been wrong in leaving her alone so long.
或许让她一个人那么久 是错误的

1270
01:52:21,430 --> 01:52:24,058
Bring her to me, even if she's not yet ready.
我想你最好把她带来见我 即使她还没准备好

1271
01:52:24,300 --> 01:52:25,961
Yes, Reverend Mother.
是的，院长

1272
01:52:31,474 --> 01:52:35,001
Sister Augusta, take our new postulant to the robing room.
加丝特修女 带这位新姐妹到更衣室

1273
01:52:36,011 --> 01:52:38,241
God bless you, my daughter.
愿上帝祝福你，我的女儿

1274
01:52:44,487 --> 01:52:46,182
Yes, bring her in.
是的，带她进来

1275
01:52:55,231 --> 01:52:57,461
You've been unhappy. I'm sorry.
你很不快乐，我很难过

1276
01:52:59,502 --> 01:53:00,696
Reverend Mother.
院长

1277
01:53:01,070 --> 01:53:03,698
Why did they send you back to us?
他们为何要你回来？

1278
01:53:04,540 --> 01:53:06,496
They didn't send me back. I left.
他们没有要我走 是我主动离开的

1279
01:53:09,011 --> 01:53:10,569
Sit down, Maria.
坐下，犸莉亚

1280
01:53:11,080 --> 01:53:12,877
Tell me what happened.
告诉我事情的始末

1281
01:53:18,087 --> 01:53:19,384
I was frightened.
是因为我害怕

1282
01:53:19,622 --> 01:53:24,116
- Frightened? Were they unkind to you. - Oh, no!
-害怕，是不是他们对你不好？ -哦，不是

1283
01:53:24,393 --> 01:53:28,090
No, I was confused. I felt...
我很迷惑，我…

1284
01:53:29,565 --> 01:53:31,624
I've never felt that way before.
我从未有那种感觉

1285
01:53:31,901 --> 01:53:35,632
I couldn't stay. I knew that here I'd be away from it. I'd be safe.
我不能留下来 我知道远离他们会比较安全

1286
01:53:35,905 --> 01:53:40,604
Maria, our abbey is not to be used as an escape.
犸莉亚，我们的修道院 不是用来逃避的

1287
01:53:40,876 --> 01:53:43,106
What is it you can't face?
是什么事令你无法面对？

1288
01:53:45,080 --> 01:53:46,513
I can't face him again.
我无法再面对他

1289
01:53:47,316 --> 01:53:48,806
Him?
他？

1290
01:53:50,452 --> 01:53:52,511
Thank you, Sister Margaretta.
谢谢你，犸格丽特修女

1291
01:54:02,097 --> 01:54:03,758
Captain von Trapp?
是范崔普先生？

1292
01:54:09,171 --> 01:54:11,901
- Are you in love with him? - I don't know!
-你是否爱上他了？ -我不知道

1293
01:54:12,141 --> 01:54:13,574
I don't know. L...
我不知道…

1294
01:54:14,143 --> 01:54:17,965
The baroness said I was. She said that he was in love with me.
男爵夫人，她说他爱上我了

1295
01:54:18,247 --> 01:54:20,841
But I didn't want to believe it.
但我不愿相信

1296
01:54:21,984 --> 01:54:24,248
There were times we looked at each other.
当我们彼此对看时

1297
01:54:24,486 --> 01:54:26,044
I could hardly breathe.
我简直不能呼吸

1298
01:54:26,355 --> 01:54:29,119
- Did you let him see your feelings? - I don't know.
-你让他知道你的感受了吗？ -我不知道

1299
01:54:29,692 --> 01:54:32,354
That's what's torturing me. I was on God's errand.
这正是折磨我的原因 我是侍奉神的

1300
01:54:32,595 --> 01:54:37,555
To have asked for his love would have been wrong. I just couldn't stay.
爱他是错的，我不能留下

1301
01:54:39,702 --> 01:54:42,557
I'm ready at this moment to take my vows.
我已作好发誓的准备

1302
01:54:43,439 --> 01:54:46,499
- Please help me. - Maria.
-请帮助我 -犸莉亚

1303
01:54:48,077 --> 01:54:52,776
The love of a man and a woman is holy. You have a great capacity to love.
男女之间的爱也是神圣的 你是可以去爱的

1304
01:54:53,015 --> 01:54:55,939
You must find out how God wants you to spend your love.
你必须了解 上帝是要你如何去爱

1305
01:54:56,185 --> 01:55:00,076
But I pledged my life to God. I pledged my life to his service.
但我已献身上帝 我要终生为上帝服务

1306
01:55:00,289 --> 01:55:04,646
My daughter, if you love this man, it doesn't mean you love God less.
我的女儿，如果你爱这个人 并不表示你就要少爱上帝了

1307
01:55:06,328 --> 01:55:08,193
No.
不

1308
01:55:08,397 --> 01:55:10,285
You must find out.
你必须找出答案

1309
01:55:12,034 --> 01:55:14,525
You must go back.
你必须要回去

1310
01:55:14,803 --> 01:55:16,464
You can't ask me to do that.
你不能要求我这样做

1311
01:55:16,639 --> 01:55:17,628
- Please let me stay. I beg... - Maria.
-拜托你，让我留下，我求求你 -犸莉亚

1312
01:55:19,675 --> 01:55:23,600
These walls were not built to shut out problems.
这些墙并不是 建造来逃避问题的

1313
01:55:23,812 --> 01:55:25,370
You have to face them.
你必须面对它

1314
01:55:25,981 --> 01:55:29,212
You have to live the life you were born to live.
你要过你本来就应过的生活

1315
01:55:35,090 --> 01:55:39,447
Climb every mountain
攀登每座山

1316
01:55:39,662 --> 01:55:43,223
Search high and low
寻遍高与低

1317
01:55:43,666 --> 01:55:48,399
Follow every byway
踏遍每条僻路

1318
01:55:48,671 --> 01:55:52,903
Every path you know
踏遍每条路

1319
01:55:53,375 --> 01:55:57,835
Climb every mountain
攀登每座山

1320
01:55:58,113 --> 01:56:02,402
Ford every stream
涉过每条小溪

1321
01:56:02,685 --> 01:56:07,042
Follow every rainbow
跟随每道彩虹

1322
01:56:07,323 --> 01:56:11,612
Till you find your dream
直至找到你的美梦

1323
01:56:11,860 --> 01:56:14,920
A dream that will need
这美梦需要你

1324
01:56:15,197 --> 01:56:20,021
All the love you can give
献出全部的爱

1325
01:56:20,769 --> 01:56:24,193
Every day of your life
在你有生之年

1326
01:56:24,440 --> 01:56:30,868
For as long as you live
一直下去

1327
