Climb every mountain
攀登每座山

1328
01:56:35,718 --> 01:56:40,041
Ford every stream
涉过每条小溪

1329
01:56:40,289 --> 01:56:44,851
Follow every rainbow
跟随每道彩虹

1330
01:56:45,094 --> 01:56:53,456
Till you find your dream
直至找到你的美梦

1331
01:56:54,603 --> 01:56:58,095
A dream that will need
这美梦需要你

1332
01:56:58,374 --> 01:57:03,937
All the love you can give
献出全部的爱

1333
01:57:04,213 --> 01:57:07,671
Every day of your life
在你有生之年

1334
01:57:07,916 --> 01:57:14,378
For as long as you live
一直下去

1335
01:57:14,623 --> 01:57:19,048
Climb every mountain
攀登每座山

1336
01:57:19,294 --> 01:57:23,219
Ford every stream
涉过每条小溪

1337
01:57:23,899 --> 01:57:28,495
Follow every rainbow
跟随每道彩虹

1338
01:57:28,937 --> 01:57:32,964
Till you find...
直至找到

1339
01:57:33,275 --> 01:57:42,570
...your dream
你的美梦

1340
01:57:45,754 --> 01:57:49,281
Now, it's not like my children to be secretive.
这样神神秘秘的 不像我的孩子

1341
01:57:49,491 --> 01:57:51,584
We're not being secretive, Father.
我们才不神秘，爸爸

1342
01:57:53,295 --> 01:57:56,628
And it's not like my children to be late for dinner.
吃饭迟到也不像我的孩子

1343
01:57:56,865 --> 01:58:00,323
- We lost track of the time. - I see.
-我们忘了时间而已 -我知道了

1344
01:58:01,136 --> 01:58:04,526
Who's going to be the first one to tell me the truth? Friedrich.
好了，谁要第一个告诉我事实？ 费瑞克

1345
01:58:04,807 --> 01:58:06,832
Brigitta. Liesl.
碧姬塔，莉莎

1346
01:58:08,243 --> 01:58:10,438
Where do you think we were, Father?
你认为我们去哪了？

1347
01:58:17,052 --> 01:58:21,011
If you don't believe us, you must have some idea of where you think we were.
如果你不相信我们 你一定是对于我们去哪有点头绪吧

1348
01:58:24,626 --> 01:58:26,389
- Marta. - Yes, Father.
-犸塔 -是的，爸爸

1349
01:58:26,628 --> 01:58:27,856
You tell me.
你来告诉我

1350
01:58:29,164 --> 01:58:32,827
Friedrich told you, Father. We were berry picking.
费瑞克告诉过你，爸爸 我们去采草莓了

1351
01:58:33,669 --> 01:58:38,299
- I forgot! You were berry picking. - Yes, we love berry picking.
-我忘了！你们去采草莓 -是呀，我们很喜欢采草莓

1352
01:58:38,640 --> 01:58:39,766
All afternoon?
整个下午？

1353
01:58:40,008 --> 01:58:41,703
- We picked thousands. - Thousands?
-是的，我们采了几千颗 -几千颗？

1354
01:58:41,910 --> 01:58:44,834
- They were all over the place. - What kind of berries?
-四处也是呢 -哪一种草莓？

1355
01:58:45,080 --> 01:58:48,379
- Blueberries, sir. - Blueberries.
-是蓝草莓，先生 -蓝草莓

1356
01:58:50,319 --> 01:58:53,675
It's too early for blueberries.
蓝草莓的季节还没到

1357
01:58:55,157 --> 01:58:57,216
- They were strawberries. - Strawberries?
-是草莓 -草莓？

1358
01:58:57,993 --> 01:59:00,689
It's been so cold lately, they turned blue.
最近很冷 所以它们变成蓝色了

1359
01:59:06,502 --> 01:59:08,697
Very well. Show me the berries.
很好，让我看草莓

1360
01:59:09,905 --> 01:59:11,167
- We... - Well...
-我们… -这个…

1361
01:59:11,406 --> 01:59:14,170
- Show me the berries you picked. - We don't have them.
-快让我看草莓 -我们没有

1362
01:59:14,409 --> 01:59:16,673
You don't have them? What happened to them?
你们没有？发生了什么事？

1363
01:59:16,912 --> 01:59:19,710
- We... - We ate them.
-我们… -我们吃了

1364
01:59:19,915 --> 01:59:22,509
- You ate them? - Yes!
-你们吃了它们？ -是啊

1365
01:59:22,718 --> 01:59:24,310
- They were so good. - Delicious.
-它们很好吃 -很好吃

1366
01:59:24,520 --> 01:59:25,748
Very well.
非常好

1367
01:59:26,021 --> 01:59:31,118
Since you've obviously stuffed yourselves on thousands of berries...
既然你们吃了几千颗的草莓

1368
01:59:31,393 --> 01:59:35,318
...you can't be hungry anymore, so I'll have to tell Frau Schmidt...
你们不可能肚子饿了 所以我可以告诉思蜜德

1369
01:59:35,564 --> 01:59:38,419
...to skip your dinner.
不用煮你们的晚餐

1370
01:59:47,609 --> 01:59:50,373
It's your fault. We should have told him the truth.
都是你的错 我们应该老实告诉他

1371
01:59:50,612 --> 01:59:52,603
And made him boiling mad at us?
让他生我们的气吗？

1372
01:59:52,848 --> 01:59:54,736
It's better than starving to death.
总比饿死好

1373
01:59:54,983 --> 01:59:57,838
We didn't do anything wrong. We just wanted to see her.
我们没有做错什么 我们只是想见她

1374
01:59:59,154 --> 02:00:02,282
My stomach's making noises.
我的肚子在咕咕叫

1375
02:00:02,724 --> 02:00:05,557
The least they could have done was to let us say hello.
他们至少可以 让我们向她打个招呼

1376
02:00:06,662 --> 02:00:09,893
- I wonder what grass tastes like. - I feel awful.
-我们不如吃草吧 -我很不开心

1377
02:00:11,100 --> 02:00:15,366
When Fraulein Maria wanted to feel better she used to sing that song.
犸莉亚不开心时便会唱那首歌 让自己心情好转的

1378
02:00:15,938 --> 02:00:17,428
Let's try it.
我们唱唱看

1379
02:00:17,639 --> 02:00:20,335
Raindrops on roses
玫瑰上的雨露

1380
02:00:20,509 --> 02:00:24,639
And whiskers on kittens
小猫的胡须

1381
02:00:25,480 --> 02:00:28,074
Bright copper kettles
光亮的铜壶

1382
02:00:28,250 --> 02:00:31,310
And warm woolen mittens
温暖的羊毛手套

1383
02:00:32,688 --> 02:00:38,649
Brown paper packages Tied up with strings
有细绳的褐色包装纸

1384
02:00:38,927 --> 02:00:44,923
These are a few of my favorite things
这些都是我心爱的事物

1385
02:00:45,167 --> 02:00:47,192
Why don't I feel better?
为什么我的心情没有好起来？

1386
02:00:48,370 --> 02:00:50,668
Girls in white dresses
女孩们穿着白裙

1387
02:00:50,939 --> 02:00:53,999
With blue satin sashes
佩着蓝缎带

1388
02:00:54,243 --> 02:00:59,931
Snowflakes that stay On my nose and eyelashes
雪花落在我的鼻子和睫毛上

1389
02:01:00,315 --> 02:01:03,443
- Silver white winters... - Fraulein Maria's back!
-银白色的冬天… -犸莉亚小姐回来了

1390
02:01:03,652 --> 02:01:04,983
...that melt into springs
溶化成春天

1391
02:01:05,387 --> 02:01:08,584
These are a few of my favorite things
这些都是我喜爱的事物

1392
02:01:08,857 --> 02:01:11,951
When the dog bites When the bee stings
当狗咬时，当蜂蛰时

1393
02:01:12,194 --> 02:01:14,321
When I'm feeling sad
当我感觉伤心时

1394
02:01:14,830 --> 02:01:17,754
I simply remember my favorite things
只要想起我最喜爱的事物

1395
02:01:18,033 --> 02:01:20,263
And then I don't feel
我的心情就不会…

1396
02:01:20,535 --> 02:01:26,826
So bad
如此糟了

1397
02:01:27,576 --> 02:01:30,602
- Children, I'm so glad to see you. - We missed you.
-孩子们，看到你们真高兴 -我们很想念你

1398
02:01:30,779 --> 02:01:31,871
I missed you.
我想念你们

1399
02:01:32,114 --> 02:01:34,241
- Kurt, how are you? - Hungry.
-寇特，你好吗？ -很饿

1400
02:01:35,784 --> 02:01:38,412
- What happened to your finger? - It got caught.
-葛特儿，你的手指怎么了？ -被割伤了

1401
02:01:38,654 --> 02:01:40,815
- Caught in what? - Friedrich's teeth.
-被什么割的？ -费端克的牙齿

1402
02:01:42,057 --> 02:01:44,252
- Liesl, you all right? - Just fair.
-莉莎，你好吗？ -还好啦

1403
02:01:44,459 --> 02:01:47,417
- Any telegrams been delivered lately? - None at all.
-最近有没有电报来？ -什么都没有

1404
02:01:47,663 --> 02:01:51,121
But I'm learning to accept it. I'll be glad when school begins.
但是我在学习接受现实 我在期待学校开学的日子

1405
02:01:51,400 --> 02:01:56,133
Liesl, you can't use school to escape your problems. You have to face them.
莉莎，你不能用学校作为逃避 问题的地方，你必须面对问题

1406
02:01:56,338 --> 02:01:57,828
I have so much to tell you.
我要告诉你们很多事

1407
02:01:57,973 --> 02:02:00,066
We have things to tell you too.
我们也有许多事要告诉你

1408
02:02:00,242 --> 02:02:03,973
The most important thing is that Father is going to be married.
最重要的是，爸爸要结婚了

1409
02:02:04,246 --> 02:02:05,338
Married?
结婚？

1410
02:02:05,614 --> 02:02:07,741
Yes, to Baroness Schraeder.
是的，是和男爵夫人

1411
02:02:15,557 --> 02:02:17,115
Oh, I see.
哦，我知道了

1412
02:02:18,960 --> 02:02:22,316
Father, look! Fraulein Maria's back!
爸爸，看！ 犸莉亚回来了！

1413
02:02:22,564 --> 02:02:24,657
Fraulein Maria's back from the abbey.
犸莉亚从修道院回来了

1414
02:02:26,802 --> 02:02:27,962
Good evening, captain.
舰长你好

1415
02:02:29,371 --> 02:02:30,770
Good evening.
你好

1416
02:02:33,175 --> 02:02:35,063
Everyone inside for dinner.
大家都进去吃晚餐

1417
02:02:35,310 --> 02:02:36,937
Dinner!
晚饭，太好了！

1418
02:02:46,288 --> 02:02:51,021
You left without saying goodbye. Even to the children.
你不辞而别 甚至没向小孩们道别

1419
02:02:51,960 --> 02:02:53,621
It was wrong of me. Forgive me.
是我的错，请原谅我

1420
02:02:55,597 --> 02:02:56,723
Why did you?
为什么要如此？

1421
02:02:56,965 --> 02:02:59,854
Please don't ask me. The reason no longer exists.
请不要问我 反正原因已经不存在了

1422
02:03:00,969 --> 02:03:04,029
Fraulein Maria, you've returned.
犸莉亚小姐，你回来了

1423
02:03:05,240 --> 02:03:07,162
Isn't it wonderful, Georg?
盖尔，这不是很好吗？

1424
02:03:10,379 --> 02:03:12,609
I wish you every happiness, baroness.
男爵夫人，我祝福你幸福快乐

1425
02:03:12,814 --> 02:03:15,647
You too, captain. The children say you're to marry.
你也是，舰长 孩子们告诉我你们要结婚了

1426
02:03:15,817 --> 02:03:16,875
Thank you, my dear.
谢谢你，亲爱的

1427
02:03:19,488 --> 02:03:23,015
You are back to stay?
你会留下吗？

1428
02:03:25,127 --> 02:03:28,426
Only until arrangements can be made for another governess.
只待到下一位老师来为止

1429
02:04:24,219 --> 02:04:25,811
There you are.
原来你在这里

1430
02:04:40,202 --> 02:04:42,727
I must speak to cook about the schnitzel.
我真的要跟你的厨师谈谈

1431
02:04:42,971 --> 02:04:46,270
It is entirely too delicious for my figure.
食物太好吃会影响我的身材

1432
02:04:46,708 --> 02:04:49,632
And it makes you much too quiet at the dinner table.
也让你在餐桌上 没说很多话

1433
02:04:49,911 --> 02:04:51,902
Or was it the wine?
是不是酒的关系？

1434
02:04:52,147 --> 02:04:53,978
Undoubtedly the wine.
一定是

1435
02:04:56,518 --> 02:04:58,816
You have no idea the trouble I'm having...
你不知道为了要送你

1436
02:04:59,087 --> 02:05:01,817
...trying to decide on a wedding present for you.
一件结婚礼物 我费尽了多少心思

1437
02:05:02,090 --> 02:05:04,251
Oh, I know. I'm enough.
我明白，你有我已经足够

1438
02:05:04,493 --> 02:05:08,156
But I do want you to have some little trifle for the occasion.
但是我一定要送你点小玩意

1439
02:05:08,363 --> 02:05:10,729
At first I thought of a fountain pen...
我首先想到的是钢笔

1440
02:05:10,966 --> 02:05:13,230
...but you've already got one.
但是你已有一支

1441
02:05:13,468 --> 02:05:16,426
Then I thought perhaps a villa in the south of France...
然后我想送你 一幢法国南部的别墅

1442
02:05:16,671 --> 02:05:19,333
...but they are so difficult to gift-wrap.
但是它很难包装起来

1443
02:05:19,608 --> 02:05:21,997
Oh, Georg, how do you feel about yachts?
你觉得游艇好吗？

1444
02:05:22,277 --> 02:05:24,541
A long, sleek one for the Mediterranean...
可以畅游地中海的那种

1445
02:05:24,813 --> 02:05:27,543
...or a tiny one for your bathtub, huh?
或是放在浴缸中的那种

1446
02:05:29,751 --> 02:05:31,776
- Elsa. - Where to go on our honeymoon?
-艾莎 -我们要去哪渡蜜月？

1447
02:05:32,020 --> 02:05:33,612
Now, that's a real problem.
这可真是个难题了

1448
02:05:33,822 --> 02:05:37,178
A trip around the world would be lovely. And then I said:
我想环游世界会很棒

1449
02:05:37,459 --> 02:05:40,314
"Oh, Elsa, there must be someplace better to go."
但一定会有更好的地方可以去

1450
02:05:40,562 --> 02:05:42,985
- But don't worry, darling, I'Il... - Elsa.
-但别担心… -艾莎

1451
02:05:43,698 --> 02:05:44,892
Yes, Georg.
是的

1452
02:05:45,967 --> 02:05:47,264
It's no use...
这是没有用的

1453
02:05:48,503 --> 02:05:49,868
...you and I.
你和我的关系

1454
02:05:51,406 --> 02:05:54,671
I'm being dishonest to both of us...
我一直都没有坦诚面对

1455
02:05:56,011 --> 02:05:57,638
...and utterly unfair to you.
你和我的关系

1456
02:06:02,884 --> 02:06:05,682
- When two people talk of marriage... - No, don't.
-当两个人谈论到婚嫁时 -不要

1457
02:06:06,555 --> 02:06:08,648
Don't say another word, please.
不要再说了，拜托你

1458
02:06:11,927 --> 02:06:16,990
You see, there are other things I've been thinking of.
我也在想其他的事

1459
02:06:17,899 --> 02:06:22,598
Fond as I am of you, I really don't think you're the right man for me.
虽然我喜欢你 但是我真的不认为你适合我

1460
02:06:25,173 --> 02:06:27,596
You're much too independent.
你太独立了

1461
02:06:27,909 --> 02:06:32,664
And I need someone who needs me desperately...
而我要一个非常需要我的人

1462
02:06:32,914 --> 02:06:35,940
...or at least needs my money desperately.
或最起码是非常需要我的钱

1463
02:06:38,119 --> 02:06:43,045
I've enjoyed every moment we've had together and I do thank you for that.
我们在一起的每一分钟 我都很快乐，为此我谢谢你

1464
02:06:45,827 --> 02:06:47,749
Now, if you'll forgive me...
失陪一下

1465
02:06:47,929 --> 02:06:50,022
...I'll go inside, pack my little bags...
我现在要进去 收拾我的行李

1466
02:06:50,198 --> 02:06:52,723
...and return to Vienna where I belong.
回到我原属的地方，维也纳

1467
02:06:58,106 --> 02:06:59,937
And somewhere out there...
那边有个人

1468
02:07:00,208 --> 02:07:04,599
...is a young lady who, I think...
是位年轻小姐，我想

1469
02:07:04,879 --> 02:07:06,107
...will never be a nun.
她做不成修女了

1470
02:07:18,259 --> 02:07:20,591
Auf Wiedersehen, darling.
亲爱的，再见了

1471
02:07:46,321 --> 02:07:47,481
Hello.
哈

1472
02:07:53,294 --> 02:07:56,889
I thought I just might find you here.
我想我可能会在这里找到你

1473
02:08:01,036 --> 02:08:03,334
Was there something you wanted?
你有什么事找我吗？

1474
02:08:03,705 --> 02:08:06,902
No, no, no. Sit down, please.
没有，没有，请坐下

1475
02:08:07,809 --> 02:08:09,174
Please.
请坐

1476
02:08:14,282 --> 02:08:15,647
May I?
我可以坐吗？

1477
02:08:28,029 --> 02:08:32,728
You know, I was thinking and I was wondering two things:
我在想… 在思索两件事情

1478
02:08:33,868 --> 02:08:38,157
Why did you run away to the abbey?
为什么你逃回修道院？

1479
02:08:38,973 --> 02:08:43,672
And what was it that made you come back?
还有，是什么事又让你回来？

1480
02:08:45,346 --> 02:08:49,737
Well, I had an obligation to fulfill...
这个，我有责任要完成

1481
02:08:50,018 --> 02:08:52,145
...and I came back to fulfill it.
我回来履行的

1482
02:08:52,754 --> 02:08:54,244
Is that all?
只是这样吗？

1483
02:08:55,557 --> 02:08:57,684
And I missed the children.
还有，我想念孩子们

1484
02:08:58,026 --> 02:08:59,220
Yes.
是的

1485
02:09:00,495 --> 02:09:03,384
- Only the children? - No. Yes.
-只有小孩们？ -不…是的

1486
02:09:03,598 --> 02:09:07,386
- Isn't it right that I missed them? - Oh, yes. Yes, of course.
-我可以想念他们，对吗？ -对…当然可以了

1487
02:09:07,669 --> 02:09:10,263
I was only hoping that perhaps you...
我只是想你或许会…

1488
02:09:11,406 --> 02:09:13,169
Perhaps you might...
或许你会…

1489
02:09:14,909 --> 02:09:16,103
Yes?
怎样？

1490
02:09:17,879 --> 02:09:23,203
Well, nothing was the same when you were away...
这个… 当你离开后一切都变了

1491
02:09:23,918 --> 02:09:27,183
...and it'll be all wrong again after you leave...
如果你又再离去 我们又会再度失落

1492
02:09:27,422 --> 02:09:32,086
...and I just thought perhaps you might change your mind.
我只是想 也许你可以改变心意留下来

1493
02:09:36,131 --> 02:09:40,363
Well, I'm sure the baroness will be able to make things fine for you.
我想男爵夫人一定会把 一切的事情都安排得很好

1494
02:09:40,602 --> 02:09:42,001
Maria...
犸莉亚

1495
02:09:44,105 --> 02:09:47,597
- There isn't going to be any baroness. - There isn't?
-再也没有什么男爵夫人了 -没有了吗？

1496
02:09:50,011 --> 02:09:51,376
No.
没有

1497
02:09:51,646 --> 02:09:53,443
I don't understand.
我不明白

1498
02:09:55,817 --> 02:09:59,947
Well, we've called off our engagement, you see, and...
我们已经解除婚约了

1499
02:10:00,221 --> 02:10:03,645
- Oh, I'm sorry. - Yes. You are?
-我很难过 -对，真的吗？

1500
02:10:04,793 --> 02:10:07,023
- You did? - Yes.
-真的？ -是的

1501
02:10:08,096 --> 02:10:12,624
Well, you can't marry someone when you're...
你不能和一个人结婚…

1502
02:10:15,136 --> 02:10:17,229
...in love with someone else...
却又爱着另一个人

1503
02:10:20,642 --> 02:10:22,075
...can you?
你可以吗？

1504
02:10:56,945 --> 02:10:59,209
The Reverend Mother always says:
院长常说

1505
02:10:59,480 --> 02:11:02,870
"When the Lord closes a door, somewhere He opens a window."
“当主关上门时 他会在某处打开窗子的”

1506
02:11:11,292 --> 02:11:14,352
What else does the Reverend Mother say?
院长还说了什么？

1507
02:11:15,296 --> 02:11:17,685
That you have to look for your life.
你需要寻求你自己的生命

1508
02:11:19,367 --> 02:11:21,858
Is that why you came back?
这是不是你回来的原因？

1509
02:11:25,907 --> 02:11:27,397
And have you found it...
你找到了吗？

1510
02:11:28,409 --> 02:11:29,603
...Maria?
犸莉亚

1511
02:11:31,346 --> 02:11:33,337
I think I have.
我想我找到了

1512
02:11:35,650 --> 02:11:36,639
I know I have.
我知道我已找到了

1513
02:11:39,954 --> 02:11:41,615
I love you.
我爱你

1514
02:11:45,593 --> 02:11:48,084
Oh, can this be happening to me?
这种事情会发生在我身上吗？

1515
02:11:50,832 --> 02:11:56,190
Perhaps I had a wicked childhood
或许我的童年是不愉快的

1516
02:11:57,705 --> 02:12:02,961
Perhaps I had a miserable youth
或许我的青春期是悲惨的

1517
02:12:04,846 --> 02:12:10,705
But somewhere In my wicked, miserable past
但在我又不愉快 又可悲的过去

1518
02:12:11,286 --> 02:12:17,077
There must have been a moment of truth
却总有一刻是真实的

1519
02:12:17,992 --> 02:12:24,784
For here you are Standing there loving me
你就站在这里 爱着我

1520
02:12:25,500 --> 02:12:31,530
Whether or not you should
不管应该与否

1521
02:12:32,273 --> 02:12:38,963
So somewhere in my youth or childhood
因此在我的童年或少年时

1522
02:12:39,814 --> 02:12:47,471
I must have done something good
一定是做过了什么好事

1523
02:12:48,723 --> 02:12:51,681
Nothing comes from nothing
万事皆有因

1524
02:12:52,827 --> 02:12:56,649
Nothing ever could
不会无中生有

1525
02:12:57,532 --> 02:13:06,395
So somewhere in my youth or childhood
因此在我的童年或少年时

1526
02:13:07,909 --> 02:13:17,398
I must have done something good
一定是做过了什么好事

1527
02:13:18,353 --> 02:13:23,177
Do you know when I first started loving you?
你知道我是何时开始 爱上你的？

1528
02:13:23,591 --> 02:13:27,448
That night at dinner, when you sat on that ridiculous pine cone.
那天晚餐 你坐在那可笑的松果上

1529
02:13:27,729 --> 02:13:29,026
What?
什么？

1530
02:13:30,365 --> 02:13:33,789
I knew the first time you blew that silly whistle.
当你吹着那个傻哨子时 我就爱上你了

1531
02:13:34,736 --> 02:13:36,727
Oh, my love.
哦，我的爱

1532
02:13:40,475 --> 02:13:48,405
For here you are Standing there loving me
你就站在这里 爱着我

1533
02:13:50,385 --> 02:13:56,176
Whether or not you should
不管应该与否

1534
02:13:57,592 --> 02:14:04,623
So somewhere in my youth or childhood
因此在我的童年或少年时

1535
02:14:05,400 --> 02:14:13,125
I must have done something good
一定是做过了什么好事

1536
02:14:14,308 --> 02:14:17,800
Nothing comes from nothing
万事皆有因

1537
02:14:18,446 --> 02:14:21,574
Nothing ever could
不会无中生有

1538
02:14:21,816 --> 02:14:27,607
So somewhere in my youth...
因此在我的童年…

1539
02:14:27,855 --> 02:14:30,119
...or childhood
或少年时

1540
02:14:33,227 --> 02:14:39,757
I must have done something
一定是做过了

1541
02:14:41,803 --> 02:14:54,466
Something good
什么好事

1542
02:15:01,155 --> 02:15:02,645
Maria.
犸莉亚

1543
02:15:04,525 --> 02:15:09,121
Is there anyone I should go to, to ask permission to marry you?
我要征求谁的同意才能娶你？

1544
02:15:13,034 --> 02:15:14,797
- Why don't we ask... - The children?
-为什么我们不问… -孩子们？

1545
02:17:03,858 --> 02:17:08,137
How do you solve a problem like Maria?
你要如何处理 像犸莉亚这样的问题人物？

1546
02:17:08,950 --> 02:17:12,681
How do you catch a cloud And pin it down?
你要如何摘下浮云 然后钉牢？

1547
02:17:13,654 --> 02:17:17,818
How do you find a word That means Maria?
你要如何用言语形容她？

1548
02:17:18,192 --> 02:17:19,284
A flibbertigibbet
捣蛋鬼

1549
02:17:19,460 --> 02:17:22,725
A will-o'-the-wisp A clown
鬼灵精 小丑

1550
02:17:22,964 --> 02:17:27,492
Many a thing you know You'd like to tell her
许多事你们想告诉她

1551
02:17:27,935 --> 02:17:31,996
Many a thing she ought to understand
许多事她该明t

1552
02:17:32,707 --> 02:17:36,996
But how do you make her stay And listen to all you say?
但如何使她停下听你说完？

1553
02:17:37,445 --> 02:17:41,302
How do you keep a wave upon the sand?
如何使海浪停留在沙滩上？

1554
02:17:41,649 --> 02:17:46,643
Oh, how do you solve A problem like Maria?
你要如何处理 像犸莉亚这样的问题人物？

1555
02:17:47,021 --> 02:17:53,654
How do you hold a moonbeam In your hand?
如何使月光在掌中停留？

1556
02:19:59,720 --> 02:20:01,312
Herr Detweiler!
你好

1557
02:20:03,891 --> 02:20:06,587
- Heil Hitler. - Oh, good afternoon, Herr Zeller.
-希特勒万岁 -午安，吉勒先生

1558
02:20:06,827 --> 02:20:10,126
Perhaps you've not heard. I am now the Gauleiter.
或许你还不知道 我现在是这里的监督

1559
02:20:10,364 --> 02:20:11,956
Heil Hitler.
希特勒万岁

1560
02:20:12,867 --> 02:20:14,027
Heil Hitler.
希特勒万岁

1561
02:20:14,301 --> 02:20:16,599
I've come from Captain von Trapp's house.
我刚从范崔普家来

1562
02:20:17,037 --> 02:20:20,632
The only one in the area not flying the Third Reich flag...
合并后只有他家不挂…

1563
02:20:20,875 --> 02:20:22,103
...since the Anschluss.
德国旗

1564
02:20:22,343 --> 02:20:24,504
- But we have dealt with that. - I don't...
-但是我们必须解决那问题 -我不…

1565
02:20:24,745 --> 02:20:27,703
The housekeeper told me that I would find you here.
管家告诉我会在这找到你

1566
02:20:27,982 --> 02:20:29,677
The only thing she'd tell me.
这是那个女人 给我的唯一情报

1567
02:20:30,184 --> 02:20:32,709
What kind of information are you looking for?
你在找什么情报？

1568
02:20:32,987 --> 02:20:34,852
When will the captain return?
舰长何时会回来？

1569
02:20:35,389 --> 02:20:39,314
Well, he's on his honeymoon trip. He's not been in touch with us.
他去渡蜜月了 他没和我们联络

1570
02:20:39,560 --> 02:20:44,384
Am I to believe he hasn't communicated with his children in over a month?
你要我相信舰长一个多月 没和他的孩子们联络？

1571
02:20:44,665 --> 02:20:46,621
How many men do you know...
监督，你认识多少人…

1572
02:20:46,801 --> 02:20:50,134
...who communicate with their children while honeymooning?
会在渡蜜月时和孩子联络？

1573
02:20:51,005 --> 02:20:54,736
Upon his return, he'll fill his proper position in the new order.
当他回来时 我们希望他接受新政府的职位

1574
02:20:55,009 --> 02:20:57,398
Naturally. And may I congratulate you...
当然了，多谢你…

1575
02:20:57,678 --> 02:21:02,274
...and your people in allowing the festival to go on tonight as planned.
和你的人们允许今晚可以 如期举行音乐节

1576
02:21:02,850 --> 02:21:06,274
Why should it not go on? Nothing in Austria has changed.
为何我们会不允许？ 奥地利什么都没改变

1577
02:21:06,554 --> 02:21:09,910
Singing and music will show this to the world.
唱歌和音乐可宣告世界

1578
02:21:10,157 --> 02:21:11,784
Austria is the same.
奥地利依然如昔

1579
02:21:12,726 --> 02:21:14,091
Heil Hitler.
希特勒万岁

1580
02:21:16,263 --> 02:21:17,855
Heil Hitler.
希特勒万岁

1581
02:21:19,533 --> 02:21:20,761
Come, let's go home.
走吧，我们回家去

1582
02:21:20,968 --> 02:21:24,460
- Why was he so cross? - Everybody's cross these days.
-为何他这么凶？ -这些日子大家都很凶

1583
02:21:24,638 --> 02:21:28,062
Maybe the flag with the black spider makes people nervous.
也许是旗上的黑蜘蛛 使人们紧张起来

1584
02:21:28,275 --> 02:21:31,199
- Will Father be in trouble? - He doesn't have to be.
-爸爸是不是有麻烦了？ -他是有选择的

1585
02:21:31,445 --> 02:21:34,175
The thing to do is to get along with everybody.
这些日子以来最重要的 是和大家和睦相处

1586
02:21:34,415 --> 02:21:36,610
Remember that tonight at the concert.
我要你们记住 尤其在今晚的演唱会上

1587
02:21:36,817 --> 02:21:39,741
Are we really going to sing before a lot of people?
今晚我们真的要 在一大堆人面前唱歌？

1588
02:21:39,954 --> 02:21:42,047
Look. The von Trapp Family Singers:
看，范崔普家庭音乐团 名字是…

1589
02:21:42,256 --> 02:21:46,818
Liesl, Friedrich, Louisa, Brigitta, Kurt, Marta and Gretl.
莉莎，费瑞克，露易莎，碧姬塔 寇特，犸塔，葛特儿

1590
02:21:47,061 --> 02:21:51,418
- Why am I always last? - Because you are the most important.
-为什么我总是排在最后？ -因为你是最重要的

1591
02:21:52,132 --> 02:21:53,724
There we go.
我们走吧

1592
02:21:59,640 --> 02:22:03,098
Are you sure Father will approve of our singing in public?
你确定爸爸 会准许我们公开演唱？

1593
02:22:03,310 --> 02:22:05,608
He'll be pleased and proud.
他会很高兴并引以为傲的

1594
02:22:06,080 --> 02:22:08,503
- Liesl, do you think so? - Don't you trust me?
-莉莎，你觉得如此吗？ -你们不信任我吗？

1595
02:22:08,749 --> 02:22:09,773
No.
不信任

1596
02:22:09,984 --> 02:22:12,077
You're a very intelligent girl.
你是个很聪明的女孩

1597
02:22:12,586 --> 02:22:14,781
Liesl. Liesl!
莉莎…

1598
02:22:15,723 --> 02:22:16,917
Rolfe!
劳夫

1599
02:22:17,925 --> 02:22:19,916
I'm so glad to see you. It's been su...
很高兴见到你，已经…

1600
02:22:20,160 --> 02:22:21,252
Good afternoon.
午安

1601
02:22:21,662 --> 02:22:24,586
Give this to your father as soon as he's home.
请你把这电报交给你父亲

1602
02:22:25,266 --> 02:22:27,131
- He's on his honeymoon. - I know.
-他正在渡蜜月呢 -我知道

1603
02:22:27,334 --> 02:22:30,667
- You do? - We make it our business to know all.
-你知道？ -干我们这行的事事都要知道

1604
02:22:31,338 --> 02:22:33,966
- Who's "we"? - See that he gets it.
-谁是“我们”？ -你要肯定他会收到

1605
02:22:34,174 --> 02:22:36,472
- What is it? - It's a telegram from Berlin.
-这是什么？ -是从柏林来的电报

1606
02:22:37,344 --> 02:22:39,835
Don't you want to deliver it yourself?
你不要亲自来交给他吗？

1607
02:22:40,314 --> 02:22:42,942
I'm occupied with more important matters.
我有更重要的事

1608
02:22:43,150 --> 02:22:45,641
And your father had better be too.
你父亲也最好能知轻重

1609
02:22:45,853 --> 02:22:47,377
But, Rolfe!
但是，劳夫！

1610
02:23:10,511 --> 02:23:12,172
Father!
爸爸…

1611
02:23:12,413 --> 02:23:15,075
- We didn't expect you so soon. - Hello, hello!
-我们没料到你这么快回来 -哈…

1612
02:23:15,349 --> 02:23:18,147
We didn't expect you home until next week!
我们以为你下星期回来！

1613
02:23:18,352 --> 02:23:23,779
- Did you bring souvenirs from Paris? - Hello! How are you?
-有在巴黎给我们买手信吗？ -你好吗？

1614
02:23:24,892 --> 02:23:26,189
Why didn't you call us?
你们为什么没有打给我们？

1615
02:23:26,393 --> 02:23:28,315
We couldn't get through.
我们试过了，但是不通

1616
02:23:28,562 --> 02:23:30,518
I had nothing to do with that.
这个我也没奈何

1617
02:23:30,798 --> 02:23:32,823
We came back as fast as we could.
我们尽快赶回来了

1618
02:23:33,167 --> 02:23:35,328
Well, well, well! We missed you!
我们很想念你们

1619
02:23:35,569 --> 02:23:37,992
- We missed you! - We missed kissing you.
-我们很想你们 -我们很想亲你们

1620
02:23:38,205 --> 02:23:41,038
We missed all the noise in the morning.
我想念你们早上的噪音

1621
02:23:41,308 --> 02:23:45,506
- Mostly, we missed hearing you sing. - Oh, you came back just in time.
-最想念的是你们的歌声 -你们回来得正巧

1622
02:23:45,713 --> 02:23:47,408
Look, Fraulein Maria...
看这个，莉亚小姐…

1623
02:23:47,681 --> 02:23:49,239
I mean Mother.
我是说妈妈

1624
02:23:49,717 --> 02:23:52,208
We're going to sing in the festival tonight.
我们今晚会在音乐节唱歌

1625
02:23:52,419 --> 02:23:54,512
We've been having a lovely time!
我们过得很快乐

1626
02:23:54,755 --> 02:23:56,848
We've been rehearsing all...
我们练习了一天

1627
02:23:58,392 --> 02:24:00,724
Surprise! Surprise!
惊喜！惊喜！

1628
02:24:01,395 --> 02:24:03,886
Surprises for you on the terrace.
里面有令你们惊喜的东西

1629
02:24:06,934 --> 02:24:08,265
We'll talk about this.
我们到里面去谈这个

1630
02:24:08,535 --> 02:24:12,824
I would've told you but you were away. I had to make a last-minute decision.
我本想要告诉你，但是你不在 我只有在最后一刻自作主张了

1631
02:24:13,107 --> 02:24:15,598
I was fortunate to enter them at all.
我还算好运气 总算赶得及报名

1632
02:24:15,843 --> 02:24:20,542
They'll be the talk of the festival. Imagine, seven children in one family!
他们必会成为话题的 试想一个家庭中的七个小孩

1633
02:24:20,748 --> 02:24:22,409
Max!
麦斯

1634
02:24:22,983 --> 02:24:25,838
Somehow I recall having made it quite clear to you...
我记得我以前 向你解释得很清楚…

1635
02:24:26,086 --> 02:24:28,782
...how I feel about my family singing in public!
我对于我家的小孩 在外面演唱的事的感觉

1636
02:24:29,056 --> 02:24:30,751
The committee was enchanted.
但是委员会听过他们唱 非常的感动

1637
02:24:30,958 --> 02:24:34,121
- What did they say? - I have never heard such enthusiasm.
-他们说了什么？ -没听过这么热情的声音

1638
02:24:34,395 --> 02:24:38,661
- Don't you think just this once...? - Absolutely out of the question.
-就一次好不好？ -绝对不可能

1639
02:24:38,932 --> 02:24:43,062
- Georg, this is for Austria. - For Austria?
-这是为了奥地利 -为了奥地利？

1640
02:24:43,437 --> 02:24:46,634
- There is no Austria! - But the Anschluss was peaceful.
-已经没有奥地利了！ -但是德奥合并得很和平

1641
02:24:46,907 --> 02:24:50,399
- Let's at least be grateful for that. - Grateful?
-我们应感到欣慰 -欣慰？

1642
02:24:52,279 --> 02:24:53,906
You know, Max...
你知道吗？麦斯

1643
02:24:54,815 --> 02:24:58,012
...sometimes I don't believe I know you.
有时候我无法相信 自己认识你

1644
02:25:00,754 --> 02:25:02,119
Father, I forgot.
爸爸，我忘了

1645
02:25:02,956 --> 02:25:04,514
This is for you.
这是给你的

1646
02:25:14,334 --> 02:25:18,327
Maria, he has got to at least pretend to work with these people.
犸莉亚，至少他必须假装 和这些人合作

1647
02:25:18,605 --> 02:25:20,095
You must convince him.
你必须说服他

1648
02:25:20,340 --> 02:25:23,104
Max, I can't ask him to be less than he is.
我不能要求他听我的话

1649
02:25:23,310 --> 02:25:26,643
Then I'll talk to him. If the children don't sing, well...
那么我和他谈 如果孩子们不参加音乐节

1650
02:25:26,914 --> 02:25:29,144
...it will be a reflection on Austria.
是一样对奥地利有损的事

1651
02:25:29,950 --> 02:25:33,306
Oh, I know. It wouldn't do me any good either.
对我也没有好处

1652
02:25:38,492 --> 02:25:41,154
Mother? That sounds so nice.
妈，可以这样叫你真好

1653
02:25:41,428 --> 02:25:44,158
- I like calling you "Mother." - I like hearing it.
-我喜欢叫你妈 -我喜欢听你叫

1654
02:25:44,364 --> 02:25:47,959
You love Father very much. I can tell you do.
你很爱爸爸，我看得出来

1655
02:25:48,135 --> 02:25:49,159
Very much.
非常爱他

1656
02:25:49,336 --> 02:25:52,669
Mother, what do you do when you think you love someone?
妈，当你认为你爱某个人时 你要怎么办？

1657
02:25:53,340 --> 02:25:58,630
I mean, when you stop loving someone or he stops loving you?
我是说当你不再爱他 或他不再爱你时

1658
02:26:01,248 --> 02:26:03,341
Well, you cry a little.
你会哭一场

1659
02:26:03,751 --> 02:26:05,878
Then you wait for the sun to come out.
等待太阳出来

1660
02:26:06,153 --> 02:26:07,518
It always does.
快乐的日子终会再来

1661
02:26:07,755 --> 02:26:11,384
There are so many things I think I should know but I don't.
有许多事情我认为我应该知道 但我却不知道

1662
02:26:11,558 --> 02:26:13,514
- I really don't. - How can you?
-真的不知道 -怎么说？

1663
02:26:13,794 --> 02:26:15,989
Sometimes I feel the world is ending.
有时我觉得世界就快完了

1664
02:26:16,230 --> 02:26:19,393
- Then you feel it's just beginning? - Yes!
-然后你觉得这才刚开始？ -是的

1665
02:26:19,600 --> 02:26:23,889
It was that way with me. And for you it will be just as wonderful.
我以前也这么觉得 对你，一切会很好的

1666
02:26:24,505 --> 02:26:25,494
Do you really think so?
你真的认为如此？

1667
02:26:27,541 --> 02:26:31,307
When you're 16 going on 17
你16岁，快17岁了

1668
02:26:31,545 --> 02:26:35,140
Waiting for life to start
人生才要开始

1669
02:26:35,816 --> 02:26:39,638
Somebody kind Who touches your mind
一个让你留下好印象的人

1670
02:26:39,887 --> 02:26:44,176
Will suddenly touch your heart
会突然触动你的心灵

1671
02:26:44,591 --> 02:26:46,320
When that happens
当这事…

1672
02:26:46,727 --> 02:26:48,683
After it happens
发生之后

1673
02:26:48,962 --> 02:26:52,750
Nothing is quite the same
一切都改变了

1674
02:26:53,033 --> 02:26:54,591
Somehow I know
我知道…

1675
02:26:54,868 --> 02:26:57,029
I'll jump up and go
我会立刻走过去

1676
02:26:57,271 --> 02:27:01,537
If ever he calls my name
若他呼唤我的名字

1677
02:27:01,775 --> 02:27:05,700
Gone are your old ideas of life
你旧日对生命的看法会变改

1678
02:27:05,979 --> 02:27:10,177
The old ideas grow dim
那些旧念头都变得黯淡

1679
02:27:10,417 --> 02:27:14,740
Lo and behold You're someone's wife
你会发现你已为人妻

1680
02:27:15,756 --> 02:27:21,752
And you belong to him
你完全属于他

1681
02:27:22,029 --> 02:27:26,295
You may think this kind of adventure
你会以为这种历险

1682
02:27:26,567 --> 02:27:30,424
Never may come to you
永不会发生在自己身上

1683
02:27:31,505 --> 02:27:36,898
Darling, 16 going on 17
亲爱的已16岁，快17岁了

1684
02:27:37,744 --> 02:27:41,874
Wait a year...
耐心等一年…

1685
02:27:42,649 --> 02:27:47,905
- I'll wait a year ...or two
-我会等一年 -或两年吧

1686
02:27:48,288 --> 02:27:55,615
Just wait a year...
只要等一年…

1687
02:27:56,563 --> 02:28:05,153
...or two
或两年

1688
02:28:07,354 --> 02:28:09,130
Liesl.
莉莎

1689
02:28:25,626 --> 02:28:26,991
What is it?
什么事情？

1690
02:28:27,928 --> 02:28:29,293
Berlin.
是柏林

1691
02:28:29,763 --> 02:28:31,628
They've offered me a commission.
他们给我委派了一项任命

1692
02:28:31,865 --> 02:28:34,425
I've been requested to accept immediately...
并要求我马上接受

1693
02:28:34,668 --> 02:28:38,661
...and report to their naval base at Bremerhaven tomorrow.
明天到北莱梅港海军基地报到

1694
02:28:39,273 --> 02:28:43,266
I knew this would happen. I didn't think it would be so soon.
我就知道这种事会发生 没料到这么快

1695
02:28:43,477 --> 02:28:47,004
To refuse them would be fatal for all of us.
拒绝的话，全家会遭到惩罚

1696
02:28:48,215 --> 02:28:52,003
And joining them would be unthinkable.
加入的话后果更难想像

1697
02:28:58,158 --> 02:28:59,955
Get the children all together.
叫小孩们都过来

1698
02:29:00,227 --> 02:29:03,492
Don't say anything to worry them. Just get them ready.
别说让他们担心的话 只要让他们准备好

1699
02:29:04,398 --> 02:29:06,821
We've got to get out of Austria...
我们必须离开奥地利

1700
02:29:08,468 --> 02:29:10,163
...and this house...
还有这所房子

1701
02:29:12,506 --> 02:29:13,905
...tonight.
就在今晚

1702
02:29:57,851 --> 02:30:00,240
This strains my back and breaks my heart...
今晚你们不唱了

1703
02:30:00,520 --> 02:30:03,353
...when I think of the children missing the festival.
真是让我伤心难过

1704
02:30:03,590 --> 02:30:06,286
By your announcement we'll be over the border.
你宣布的时候 我们就越过边界了

1705
02:30:06,560 --> 02:30:08,949
Do you appreciate the sacrifice I'm making?
我希望你会感激我所做的牺牲

1706
02:30:09,196 --> 02:30:10,458
You have no choice.
你没有选择

1707
02:30:10,731 --> 02:30:13,564
I know. That's why I'm making it.
我知道，这就是我会这样做的原因

1708
02:30:14,234 --> 02:30:16,395
Why doesn't Father turn the motor on?
爸爸为何不发动引擎？

1709
02:30:16,603 --> 02:30:20,027
Because he doesn't want anyone to hear us.
因为他不要任何人听到

1710
02:30:23,610 --> 02:30:26,101
What will Frau Schmidt and Franz say?
管家们会说什么？

1711
02:30:26,380 --> 02:30:29,872
They'll be able to answer honestly they didn't know anything.
他们可以老实回答 他们什么都不知道

1712
02:30:30,117 --> 02:30:34,315
- Will we be coming back here? - Someday, Liesl. I do hope someday.
-我们会再回来吗？ -莉莎，我希望会有这一天

1713
02:30:34,588 --> 02:30:39,480
Are Father and Uncle Max going to push the car all the way to Switzerland?
爸爸和麦伯伯 要一直推车到瑞士吗？

1714
02:31:06,286 --> 02:31:08,709
Something wrong with your car, captain?
舰长，你的车是不是有毛病？

1715
02:31:09,022 --> 02:31:11,320
Yes, we couldn't get it started.
是的，车子无法启动

1716
02:31:15,095 --> 02:31:16,323
Karl.
卡尔

1717
02:31:18,298 --> 02:31:21,756
Fix Captain von Trapp's car so that it will start.
替舰长把车修好 好让其启动

1718
02:31:44,958 --> 02:31:46,789
Excellent, Karl.
做得好

1719
02:31:50,163 --> 02:31:53,291
I've not asked you where you and your family are going.
我没问你和你的家人要到哪

1720
02:31:53,834 --> 02:31:55,961
Nor have you asked me why I'm here.
你也没问我为何在此

1721
02:31:56,169 --> 02:31:59,900
Apparently we both suffer from a deplorable lack of curiosity.
我想我们两个都没什么好奇心

1722
02:32:00,807 --> 02:32:03,298
You never answered the telegram...
你没有回湍欠狻

1723
02:32:03,510 --> 02:32:06,809
...from the Admiral of the Navy of the Third Reich.
来自第三帝国海军基地的电报

1724
02:32:07,047 --> 02:32:09,538
I was under the impression, Herr Zeller...
据我所知，在奥地利

1725
02:32:09,716 --> 02:32:13,277
...that the contents of telegrams in Austria are private!
电报的内容是私人的

1726
02:32:13,987 --> 02:32:17,514
At least, the Austria I know.
最少在我所知的奥地利是如此

1727
02:32:18,658 --> 02:32:20,285
I have my orders...
我奉命…

1728
02:32:20,527 --> 02:32:22,688
...to take you to Bremerhaven tonight...
今晚带你去基地

1729
02:32:22,929 --> 02:32:25,159
...where you will accept your commission.
接受你的职务

1730
02:32:26,299 --> 02:32:31,692
I'm afraid that's going to be quite impossible.
我怕不可能了

1731
02:32:32,339 --> 02:32:34,034
You see, we...
你看…

1732
02:32:34,608 --> 02:32:37,441
...all of us, the entire family, will be...
我们全家…

1733
02:32:38,545 --> 02:32:40,570
...singing in the festival tonight.
今晚要在音乐会上演唱

1734
02:32:40,881 --> 02:32:43,304
As a matter of fact, we're going now.
事实上我们现在就要去

1735
02:32:43,950 --> 02:32:46,839
We couldn't possibly let them down now.
不可能现在让他们失望的

1736
02:32:47,053 --> 02:32:49,942
- I just hope we're not too late. - Yes.
-我希望我们不会迟到 -是的

1737
02:32:50,257 --> 02:32:53,215
You ask me to believe that you, Captain von Trapp...
你叫我相信，你舰长…

1738
02:32:53,393 --> 02:32:54,883
...are singing in a concert?
要去演唱会唱歌？

1739
02:32:55,262 --> 02:32:59,392
Believe me, it will be a performance beyond anything even I've dreamt of.
相信我，这会是最棒的表演

1740
02:32:59,733 --> 02:33:04,397
Like you, Herr Zeller, I, too, am a man of hidden talents.
吉勒先生，像你一样 我也是身怀绝技的

1741
02:33:05,071 --> 02:33:06,436
Yes.
是的

1742
02:33:06,706 --> 02:33:09,129
Here, program.
这是节目表

1743
02:33:14,214 --> 02:33:16,478
It says only the names of the children.
上面只有孩子的名字

1744
02:33:16,750 --> 02:33:20,049
It says the von Trapp Family Singers...
上面说范崔普家庭歌团

1745
02:33:20,287 --> 02:33:23,347
...and I am the head of the von Trapp family, am I not?
而我是范崔普家的头儿 不是吗？

1746
02:33:25,625 --> 02:33:29,413
And these travel clothes that you're all wearing?
穿着这些旅行装？

1747
02:33:30,263 --> 02:33:31,787
Our costumes, naturally.
是我们的制服

1748
02:33:32,065 --> 02:33:35,421
This night air is not good for the children's voices.
今晚天气不好 穿礼服会对孩子的嗓子有影响

1749
02:33:41,675 --> 02:33:45,236
Well, a slight delay in my orders will not be serious.
稍微延迟执行命令没什么大不了

1750
02:33:46,446 --> 02:33:47,936
Therefore...
你们

1751
02:33:48,815 --> 02:33:50,442
...you will sing.
去唱吧

1752
02:33:51,384 --> 02:33:53,375
You will all sing.
你们全部都要唱

1753
02:33:53,753 --> 02:33:56,278
But only because that's what I want.
这正是我希望的

1754
02:33:57,157 --> 02:34:00,649
It will demonstrate that nothing in Austria has changed.
这表示奥地利一切都没有改变

1755
02:34:01,394 --> 02:34:03,589
And when you have finished singing...
你们唱完后

1756
02:34:03,897 --> 02:34:07,025
...you, Captain von Trapp, will be taken to Bremerhaven.
我就要带舰长到北莱梅港

1757
02:34:08,335 --> 02:34:11,099
Now, if you will all get into your car...
现在，你们上车吧

1758
02:34:11,304 --> 02:34:15,092
...we will escort the von Trapp Family Singers to the festival.
我们要护送 范崔普家庭歌团去演唱会

1759
02:34:15,976 --> 02:34:18,171
No escort will be necessary.
吉勒先生，用不着护送

1760
02:34:18,345 --> 02:34:20,905
Necessary? A pleasure, captain.
舰长，我们乐意如此

1761
02:34:21,815 --> 02:34:25,672
After all, we would not want you to get lost in the crowds.
我们不希望你们迷了路

1762
02:34:26,920 --> 02:34:28,410
Would we?
对吗？

1763
02:34:29,055 --> 02:34:30,215
No.
是的

1764
02:34:46,220 --> 02:34:49,638
Sew, a needle pulling thread
Sew是用针拉着线

1765
02:34:49,843 --> 02:34:53,040
La, a note to follow sew
La是Sew之后的音

1766
02:34:53,313 --> 02:34:56,737
Tea, a drink with jam and bread
Tea是配果酱面包的饮品

1767
02:34:56,983 --> 02:35:00,749
A drink with jam and bread
是配果酱面包的饮品

1768
02:35:10,363 --> 02:35:12,490
Tea with jam Jam and bread
果酱面包

1769
02:35:18,405 --> 02:35:21,738
- With jam - A, B, C
-配果酱 -A，B，C

1770
02:35:21,975 --> 02:35:25,206
- With jam - Do-re-mi
-配果酱 -Do remi

1771
02:35:25,412 --> 02:35:29,007
Tea with jam and bread
Tea是配果酱面包的饮品

1772
02:35:29,249 --> 02:35:30,580
With jam and bread
配果酱面包

1773
02:35:30,850 --> 02:35:32,374
With jam With jam...
配果酱…

1774
02:35:32,585 --> 02:35:40,515
...and bread
面包

1775
02:36:03,350 --> 02:36:06,547
My fellow Austrians...
各位奥地利兄弟们

1776
02:36:07,854 --> 02:36:12,348
...I shall not be seeing you again, perhaps for a very long time.
或许我会有一段时间 见不到你们了

1777
02:36:13,793 --> 02:36:15,590
I would like to sing for you now...
现在我要为你们唱…

1778
02:36:17,063 --> 02:36:18,621
...a love song.
一首爱之歌

1779
02:36:20,600 --> 02:36:22,795
I know you share this love.
我知道你们会分享此爱

1780
02:36:24,104 --> 02:36:27,801
I pray that you will never let it die.
我祈求你们永远不会让它逝去

1781
02:36:40,553 --> 02:36:44,045
Edelweiss
火绒草

1782
02:36:44,257 --> 02:36:47,488
Edelweiss
火绒草

1783
02:36:47,761 --> 02:36:53,449
Every morning you greet me
每日清晨你向我打招呼

1784
02:36:53,867 --> 02:36:56,961
Small and white
小而白

1785
02:36:57,203 --> 02:37:00,001
Clean and bright
洁而亮

1786
02:37:00,573 --> 02:37:05,806
You look happy to meet me
遇见我时多欢悦

1787
02:37:06,446 --> 02:37:08,471
Blossom of snow
雪一般的花儿

1788
02:37:08,715 --> 02:37:12,310
May you bloom and grow
愿你含苞茁长

1789
02:37:12,585 --> 02:37:18,217
Bloom and grow forever
永远地含苞茁长

1790
02:37:19,692 --> 02:37:22,217
Edelweiss
火绒草

1791
02:37:22,495 --> 02:37:25,123
Edelweiss
火绒草

1792
02:37:25,331 --> 02:37:31,327
Bless my homeland forever
永远守护我的家乡

1793
02:37:35,842 --> 02:37:38,902
Edelweiss
火绒草

1794
02:37:39,179 --> 02:37:40,510
Edel...
火绒…

1795
02:37:47,887 --> 02:37:50,981
Small and white
小而白

1796
02:37:51,191 --> 02:37:54,024
Clean and bright
洁而亮

1797
02:37:54,260 --> 02:37:59,584
You look happy to meet me
遇见我时多欢悦

1798
02:38:00,433 --> 02:38:02,389
Blossom of snow
雪一般的花儿

1799
02:38:02,635 --> 02:38:06,025
May you bloom and grow
愿你含苞茁长

1800
02:38:06,706 --> 02:38:12,667
Bloom and grow forever
永远地含苞茁长

1801
02:38:13,179 --> 02:38:16,034
Edelweiss
火绒草

1802
02:38:16,382 --> 02:38:19,078
Edelweiss
火绒草

1803
02:38:19,752 --> 02:38:27,944
Bless my homeland forever
永远守护我的家乡

1804
02:38:45,745 --> 02:38:47,303
I think it'll work.
我想会行得通的

1805
02:38:48,014 --> 02:38:49,811
I shall miss all of you.
我会想念你们

1806
02:38:50,283 --> 02:38:52,774
I shall miss the money I could have made with you.
和可以从你们身上赚到的钱

1807
02:38:56,155 --> 02:38:57,645
Thank you, ladies and gentlemen.
谢谢各位先生女士

1808
02:38:58,458 --> 02:39:01,120
The competition has come to its conclusion...
比赛就要结束

1809
02:39:01,361 --> 02:39:04,489
...except, we don't know yet what that conclusion will be.
只是还不知道 最终结果会是什么

1810
02:39:05,465 --> 02:39:07,990
And while the judges arrive at their decision...
当裁判们忙于评分之时

1811
02:39:08,268 --> 02:39:11,294
...I have been given permission to offer you an encore.
我被允许再来一次安哥

1812
02:39:11,538 --> 02:39:14,769
This will be the last opportunity the von Trapps will have...
这是范崔普家庭

1813
02:39:15,008 --> 02:39:17,374
...of singing together for a long, long time.
最后一次合唱 此后，大概不会再有机会了

1814
02:39:18,478 --> 02:39:22,471
Even now, officials are waiting in this auditorium...
现在，官员正等着

1815
02:39:22,749 --> 02:39:25,445
...to escort Captain von Trapp to his new command...
护送范崔普舰长

1816
02:39:25,652 --> 02:39:29,247
...in the naval forces of the Third Reich.
向第三帝国的海军基地报到

1817
02:39:33,893 --> 02:39:38,387
And so, ladies and gentlemen, the family von Trapp again...
所以各位先生女士 范崔普家庭…

1818
02:39:39,065 --> 02:39:41,295
...to bid you farewell.
再一次向你们告别

1819
02:39:48,541 --> 02:39:52,170
There's a sad sort of clanging From the clock in the hall
忧愁的钟声来自大厅

1820
02:39:52,445 --> 02:39:55,778
And the bells in the steeple too
塔尖的钟声也响起了

1821
02:39:56,282 --> 02:40:00,104
And up in the nursery An absurd little bird
在孩子们卧室里 一只滑稽的小鸟

1822
02:40:00,353 --> 02:40:02,776
Is popping out to say "coo-coo"
伸出头来道咕咕

1823
02:40:02,989 --> 02:40:04,650
Coo-coo
咕咕

1824
02:40:04,891 --> 02:40:05,949
Coo-coo
咕咕

1825
02:40:06,159 --> 02:40:07,786
Regretfully they tell us
很抱歉他告诉我们

1826
02:40:07,994 --> 02:40:09,791
But firmly they compel us
要我们向大家…

1827
02:40:10,029 --> 02:40:12,793
To say goodbye
道晚安

1828
02:40:12,999 --> 02:40:18,164
To you
向大家

1829
02:40:21,074 --> 02:40:24,669
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, good night
别了，再见，珍重晚安

1830
02:40:24,911 --> 02:40:28,677
We hate to go And miss this pretty sight
我不愿离开如斯美景

1831
02:40:34,854 --> 02:40:38,415
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, adieu
别了，再见，珍重再见

1832
02:40:38,658 --> 02:40:42,321
Adieu, adieu To you and you and you
我向你和你和你说声再见

1833
02:40:48,601 --> 02:40:52,196
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, goodbye
别了，再见，珍重再见

1834
02:40:52,405 --> 02:40:54,066
We flit, we float
我展翅，我飘浮

1835
02:40:54,307 --> 02:40:56,002
We fleetly flee, we fly
我地消失，我在飞翔

1836
02:41:02,382 --> 02:41:06,170
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, goodbye
别了，再见，珍重再见

1837
02:41:06,386 --> 02:41:09,742
The sun has gone to bed And so must I
太阳已就，我也一样

1838
02:41:10,023 --> 02:41:13,811
Goodbye
再见

1839
02:41:14,060 --> 02:41:19,748
Goodbye
再见

1840
02:41:19,966 --> 02:41:25,199
Goodbye
再见

1841
02:41:25,438 --> 02:41:32,594
Goodbye
再见

1842
02:42:04,410 --> 02:42:08,540
Ladies and gentlemen, I have here the decision of our distinguished judges.
各位先生女士 我手上有了裁判的决定

1843
02:42:08,781 --> 02:42:11,341
We will start with the award for third prize.
我们先公布第三名

1844
02:42:11,984 --> 02:42:14,316
For this honor, the judges have named...
我有幸向你们宣布裁判决定

1845
02:42:14,554 --> 02:42:19,184
...the first soloist of the choir of St. Agatha's Church in Murback.
第三名的得主 是圣雅嘉佛合唱团的第一独唱者

1846
02:42:19,459 --> 02:42:21,689
Fraulein Schweiger.
史莱瓦格小姐

1847
02:42:58,564 --> 02:43:02,523
Second prize to The Toby Reiser Quintet.
第二名是图比莱撒四重唱

1848
02:43:30,530 --> 02:43:34,694
And the first prize, the highest honor in all Austria...
第一名，奥地利的最高荣誉奖…

1849
02:43:34,934 --> 02:43:38,028
...the von Trapp Family Singers.
范崔普家庭歌团

1850
02:43:50,383 --> 02:43:52,078
The family von Trapp.
范崔普家庭

1851
02:44:06,666 --> 02:44:07,758
They're gone!
他们走了

1852
02:44:26,452 --> 02:44:27,851
Come with me.
跟我来

1853
02:44:31,691 --> 02:44:33,682
Quickly, quickly.
快点，快点

1854
02:44:34,627 --> 02:44:36,822
I have a place you can hide.
我有个地方可让你们躲藏

1855
02:44:37,563 --> 02:44:40,794
Slowly, slowly.
慢慢来…

1856
02:44:51,811 --> 02:44:53,506
Open this gate.
把大门打开

1857
02:44:54,647 --> 02:44:56,205
Good evening.
晚安

1858
02:44:58,718 --> 02:45:00,208
Hurry up, woman.
女人，快一点

1859
02:45:20,039 --> 02:45:21,267
Two men in there.
两个人到里面去

1860
02:45:21,440 --> 02:45:23,328
Six of you cover the yard.
六个人去庭院

1861
02:45:23,542 --> 02:45:25,840
You two, cover the corridor.
你们两人去走廊

1862
02:45:40,326 --> 02:45:43,887
Reverend Mother, we didn't realize we put the abbey in this danger.
院长，没想到连累了修道院

1863
02:45:44,163 --> 02:45:46,688
No, Maria, it was right for you to come here.
不，犸莉亚，你们来是对的

1864
02:45:46,899 --> 02:45:48,764
We thought we might borrow your car.
我们想借用你们的车

1865
02:45:49,001 --> 02:45:50,889
I'm afraid our car will do you no good now.
你们用不着车了

1866
02:45:51,504 --> 02:45:53,165
I've been listening to the wires.
我听无线电说

1867
02:45:53,372 --> 02:45:55,863
The borders have just been closed.
边界被封锁了

1868
02:46:01,747 --> 02:46:04,011
All right, if the borders are closed...
好吧，边界被封锁了

1869
02:46:05,284 --> 02:46:08,640
...then we'll drive up into the hills and go over the mountains on foot.
那么我们开车到山里 再徒步过去

1870
02:46:09,221 --> 02:46:11,212
- The children... - We'll help them.
-和小孩们？ -我们会帮他们的

1871
02:46:11,457 --> 02:46:13,652
We can do it without help, Father.
爸爸，我们不需要帮助

1872
02:46:14,727 --> 02:46:16,092
Maria.
犸莉亚

1873
02:46:16,762 --> 02:46:19,424
You will not be alone. Remember:
你不会孤独无助的，记住

1874
02:46:19,665 --> 02:46:22,725
"I will lift up mine eyes unto the hills from whence cometh my help."
“我要向山举目 我的帮助从何而来”

1875
02:46:23,736 --> 02:46:24,794
Yes, Mother.
是的，院长

1876
02:46:26,205 --> 02:46:28,366
- I'm scared. - Me too.
-我好害怕 -我也是

1877
02:46:40,453 --> 02:46:41,613
God be with you.
愿主与你同在

1878
02:46:48,561 --> 02:46:50,085
- Mother. - Yes?
-妈 -是的？

1879
02:46:50,329 --> 02:46:53,560
Would it help if we sang about our favorite things?
如我们唱“心爱的事物” 会有帮助吗？

1880
02:46:53,799 --> 02:46:56,791
No, darling. This is one time it would not help.
不，亲爱的 这是唯一帮不上忙的一次

1881
02:46:57,069 --> 02:47:00,266
You must be very quiet. Hold tight to me.
你必须很安静，紧抱着我

1882
02:49:14,874 --> 02:49:16,102
Let's try the roof.
我们到屋顶看看

1883
02:50:12,331 --> 02:50:14,629
Rolfe, please.
劳夫，求求你

1884
02:50:19,638 --> 02:50:21,230
No, wait.
不要，等一下

1885
02:50:30,983 --> 02:50:32,348
Maria.
犸莉亚

1886
02:50:33,452 --> 02:50:34,851
Children.
孩子们

1887
02:50:38,924 --> 02:50:41,950
It's you we want, not them.
我们要的只是你

1888
02:50:42,328 --> 02:50:44,023
Put that down.
把那个放下

1889
02:50:45,130 --> 02:50:48,429
Not another move, or I'll shoot.
不准动，否则我就开枪

1890
02:50:50,135 --> 02:50:52,160
You're only a boy.
你只是个孩子

1891
02:50:55,174 --> 02:50:58,837
- You don't really belong to them. - Stay where you are.
-你并不是他们的人 -站在原地

1892
02:51:00,579 --> 02:51:02,570
Come away with us.
跟我们逃吧

1893
02:51:03,849 --> 02:51:05,009
Before it's too late.
现在还来得及

1894
02:51:05,584 --> 02:51:07,950
Not another step. I'll kill you.
你再行一步，我就杀了你

1895
02:51:10,222 --> 02:51:13,521
- You give that to me, Rolfe. - Did you hear me?
-把枪给我，劳夫 -你有没有听到？

1896
02:51:14,560 --> 02:51:16,152
I'll kill you.
我会杀了你

1897
02:51:18,030 --> 02:51:19,520
Rolfe.
劳夫

1898
02:51:37,850 --> 02:51:39,215
You'll never be one of them.
你永远不会跟他们一样

1899
02:51:41,987 --> 02:51:43,682
Lieutenant!
中尉

1900
02:51:43,922 --> 02:51:45,048
They're here!
他们在这里

1901
02:51:45,257 --> 02:51:46,781
They're here, lieutenant!
他们在这里，中尉

1902
02:52:28,133 --> 02:52:29,760
Reverend Mother.
院长

1903
02:52:31,103 --> 02:52:32,900
I have sinned.
我有罪

1904
02:52:34,106 --> 02:52:36,233
I too, Reverend Mother.
院长，我也是

1905
02:52:37,910 --> 02:52:40,174
What is this sin, my children?
孩子们，是什么罪？

